66struct ConstrainedTmp {
67 ConstrainedTmp() = default;
68 ConstrainedTmp(Tmp tmp)
69 : ConstrainedTmp(tmp, tmp.isReg() ? B3::ValueRep::reg(tmp.reg()) : B3::ValueRep::SomeRegister)
70 { }
71
72 ConstrainedTmp(Tmp tmp, B3::ValueRep rep)
73 : tmp(tmp)
74 , rep(rep)
75 {
76 }
77
78 explicit operator bool() const { return !!tmp; }
79
80 Tmp tmp;
81 B3::ValueRep rep;
82};
83
84class TypedTmp {
85public:
86 constexpr TypedTmp()
87 : m_tmp()
88 , m_type(Types::Void)
89 {
90 }
91
92 TypedTmp(Tmp tmp, Type type)
93 : m_tmp(tmp)
94 , m_type(type)
95 { }
96
97 TypedTmp(const TypedTmp&) = default;
98 TypedTmp(TypedTmp&&) = default;
99 TypedTmp& operator=(TypedTmp&&) = default;
100 TypedTmp& operator=(const TypedTmp&) = default;
101
102 bool operator==(const TypedTmp& other) const
103 {
104 return m_tmp == other.m_tmp && m_type == other.m_type;
105 }
106 bool operator!=(const TypedTmp& other) const
107 {
108 return !(*this == other);
109 }
110
111 explicit operator bool() const { return !!tmp(); }
112
113 operator Tmp() const { return tmp(); }
114 operator Arg() const { return Arg(tmp()); }
115 Tmp tmp() const { return m_tmp; }
116 Type type() const { return m_type; }
117
118 void dump(PrintStream& out) const
119 {
120 out.print("(", m_tmp, ", ", m_type.kind, ", ", m_type.index, ")");
121 }
122
123private:
124
125 Tmp m_tmp;
126 Type m_type;
127};

129class AirIRGenerator {
130public:
131 using ExpressionType = TypedTmp;
132 using ResultList = Vector<ExpressionType, 8>;

134 struct ControlData {
135 ControlData(B3::Origin origin, BlockSignature result, ResultList resultTmps, BlockType type, BasicBlock* continuation, BasicBlock* special = nullptr)
136 : controlBlockType(type)
137 , continuation(continuation)
138 , special(special)
139 , results(resultTmps)
140 , returnType(result)
141 {
142 UNUSED_PARAM(origin);
143 }
144
145 ControlData()
146 {
147 }
148
149 static bool isIf(const ControlData& control) { return control.blockType() == BlockType::If; }
150 static bool isTopLevel(const ControlData& control) { return control.blockType() == BlockType::TopLevel; }
151
152 void dump(PrintStream& out) const
153 {
154 switch (blockType()) {
155 case BlockType::If:
156 out.print("If: ");
157 break;
158 case BlockType::Block:
159 out.print("Block: ");
160 break;
161 case BlockType::Loop:
162 out.print("Loop: ");
163 break;
164 case BlockType::TopLevel:
165 out.print("TopLevel: ");
166 break;
167 }
168 out.print("Continuation: ", *continuation, ", Special: ");
169 if (special)
170 out.print(*special);
171 else
172 out.print("None");
173
174 CommaPrinter comma(", ", " Result Tmps: [");
175 for (const auto& tmp : results)
176 out.print(comma, tmp);
177 if (comma.didPrint())
178 out.print("]");
179 }
180
181 BlockType blockType() const { return controlBlockType; }
182 BlockSignature signature() const { return returnType; }
183
184 BasicBlock* targetBlockForBranch()
185 {
186 if (blockType() == BlockType::Loop)
187 return special;
188 return continuation;
189 }
190
191 void convertIfToBlock()
192 {
193 ASSERT(blockType() == BlockType::If);
194 controlBlockType = BlockType::Block;
195 special = nullptr;
196 }
197
198 SignatureArgCount branchTargetArity() const
199 {
200 if (blockType() == BlockType::Loop)
201 return returnType->argumentCount();
202 return returnType->returnCount();
203 }
204
205 Type branchTargetType(unsigned i) const
206 {
207 ASSERT(i < branchTargetArity());
208 if (blockType() == BlockType::Loop)
209 return returnType->argument(i);
210 return returnType->returnType(i);
211 }
212
213 private:
214 friend class AirIRGenerator;
215 BlockType controlBlockType;
216 BasicBlock* continuation;
217 BasicBlock* special;
218 ResultList results;
219 BlockSignature returnType;
220 };

350 ALWAYS_INLINE void validateInst(Inst& inst)
351 {
352 if (ASSERT_ENABLED) {
353 if (!inst.isValidForm()) {
354 dataLogLn("Inst validation failed:");
355 dataLogLn(inst, "\n");
356 if (inst.origin)
357 dataLogLn(deepDump(inst.origin), "\n");
358 CRASH();
359 }
360 }
361 }

363 static Arg extractArg(const TypedTmp& tmp) { return tmp.tmp(); }
364 static Arg extractArg(const Tmp& tmp) { return Arg(tmp); }
365 static Arg extractArg(const Arg& arg) { return arg; }

367 template<typename... Arguments>
368 void append(BasicBlock* block, Kind kind, Arguments&&... arguments)
369 {
370 // FIXME: Find a way to use origin here.
371 auto& inst = block->append(kind, nullptr, extractArg(arguments)...);
372 validateInst(inst);
373 }

397 Tmp newTmp(B3::Bank bank)
398 {
399 switch (bank) {
400 case B3::GP:
401 if (m_freeGPs.size())
402 return m_freeGPs.takeLast();
403 break;
404 case B3::FP:
405 if (m_freeFPs.size())
406 return m_freeFPs.takeLast();
407 break;
408 }
409 return m_code.newTmp(bank);
410 }
411
412 TypedTmp g32() { return { newTmp(B3::GP), Types::I32 }; }
413 TypedTmp g64() { return { newTmp(B3::GP), Types::I64 }; }
414 TypedTmp gExternref() { return { newTmp(B3::GP), Types::Externref }; }
415 TypedTmp gFuncref() { return { newTmp(B3::GP), Types::Funcref }; }
416 TypedTmp gTypeIdx(Type type) { return { newTmp(B3::GP), type }; }
417 TypedTmp f32() { return { newTmp(B3::FP), Types::F32 }; }
418 TypedTmp f64() { return { newTmp(B3::FP), Types::F64 }; }
419
420 TypedTmp tmpForType(Type type)
421 {
422 switch (type.kind) {
423 case TypeKind::I32:
424 return g32();
425 case TypeKind::I64:
426 return g64();
427 case TypeKind::Funcref:
428 return gFuncref();
429 case TypeKind::TypeIdx:
430 return gTypeIdx(type);
431 case TypeKind::Externref:
432 return gExternref();
433 case TypeKind::F32:
434 return f32();
435 case TypeKind::F64:
436 return f64();
437 case TypeKind::Void:
438 return { };
439 default:
440 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
441 }
442 }
443
444 ResultList tmpsForSignature(BlockSignature signature)
445 {
446 ResultList result(signature->returnCount());
447 for (unsigned i = 0; i < signature->returnCount(); ++i)
448 result[i] = tmpForType(signature->returnType(i));
449 return result;
450 }

456 m_patchpoints.add(result);
457 return result;
458 }

474 emitPatchpoint(basicBlock, patch, Vector<Tmp, 8> { result }, Vector<ConstrainedTmp>());

476
477 template <typename ResultTmpType, size_t inlineSize>
478 void emitPatchpoint(BasicBlock* basicBlock, B3::PatchpointValue* patch, const Vector<ResultTmpType, 8>& results, Vector<ConstrainedTmp, inlineSize>&& args)
479 {
480 if (!m_patchpointSpecial)
481 m_patchpointSpecial = static_cast<B3::PatchpointSpecial*>(m_code.addSpecial(makeUnique<B3::PatchpointSpecial>()));
482
483 auto toTmp = [&] (ResultTmpType tmp) {
484 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<ResultTmpType, Tmp>)
485 return tmp;
486 else
487 return tmp.tmp();
488 };
489
490 Inst inst(Patch, patch, Arg::special(m_patchpointSpecial));
491 Vector<Inst, 1> resultMovs;
492 switch (patch->type().kind()) {
493 case B3::Void:
494 break;
495 default: {
496 ASSERT(results.size());
497 for (unsigned i = 0; i < results.size(); ++i) {
498 switch (patch->resultConstraints[i].kind()) {
499 case B3::ValueRep::StackArgument: {
500 Arg arg = Arg::callArg(patch->resultConstraints[i].offsetFromSP());
501 inst.args.append(arg);
502 resultMovs.append(Inst(B3::Air::moveForType(m_proc.typeAtOffset(patch->type(), i)), nullptr, arg, toTmp(results[i])));
503 break;
504 }
505 case B3::ValueRep::Register: {
506 inst.args.append(Tmp(patch->resultConstraints[i].reg()));
507 resultMovs.append(Inst(B3::Air::relaxedMoveForType(m_proc.typeAtOffset(patch->type(), i)), nullptr, Tmp(patch->resultConstraints[i].reg()), toTmp(results[i])));
508 break;
509 }
510 case B3::ValueRep::SomeRegister: {
511 inst.args.append(toTmp(results[i]));
512 break;
513 }
514 default:
515 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
516 }
517 }
518 }
519 }
520
521 for (unsigned i = 0; i < args.size(); ++i) {
522 ConstrainedTmp& tmp = args[i];
523 // FIXME: This is less than ideal to create dummy values just to satisfy Air's
524 // validation. We should abstrcat Patch enough so ValueRep's don't need to be
525 // backed by Values.
526 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=194040
527 B3::Value* dummyValue = m_proc.addConstant(B3::Origin(), tmp.tmp.isGP() ? B3::Int64 : B3::Double, 0);
528 patch->append(dummyValue, tmp.rep);
529 switch (tmp.rep.kind()) {
530 case B3::ValueRep::ColdAny: // B3::Value propagates ColdAny information and later Air will allocate appropriate stack.
531 case B3::ValueRep::SomeRegister:
532 inst.args.append(tmp.tmp);
533 break;
534 case B3::ValueRep::Register:
535 patch->earlyClobbered().clear(tmp.rep.reg());
536 append(basicBlock, tmp.tmp.isGP() ? Move : MoveDouble, tmp.tmp, tmp.rep.reg());
537 inst.args.append(Tmp(tmp.rep.reg()));
538 break;
539 case B3::ValueRep::StackArgument: {
540 ASSERT(!patch->effects.terminal);
541 Arg arg = Arg::callArg(tmp.rep.offsetFromSP());
542 append(basicBlock, tmp.tmp.isGP() ? Move : MoveDouble, tmp.tmp, arg);
543 ASSERT(arg.canRepresent(patch->child(i)->type()));
544 inst.args.append(arg);
545 break;
546 }
547 default:
548 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
549 }
550 }
551
552 for (auto valueRep : patch->resultConstraints) {
553 if (valueRep.isReg())
554 patch->lateClobbered().clear(valueRep.reg());
555 }
556 for (unsigned i = patch->numGPScratchRegisters; i--;)
557 inst.args.append(g64().tmp());
558 for (unsigned i = patch->numFPScratchRegisters; i--;)
559 inst.args.append(f64().tmp());
560
561 validateInst(inst);
562 basicBlock->append(WTFMove(inst));
563 for (Inst result : resultMovs) {
564 validateInst(result);
565 basicBlock->append(WTFMove(result));
566 }
567 }
568
569 template <typename Branch, typename Generator>
570 void emitCheck(const Branch& makeBranch, const Generator& generator)
571 {
572 // We fail along the truthy edge of 'branch'.
573 Inst branch = makeBranch();
574
575 // FIXME: Make a hashmap of these.
576 B3::CheckSpecial::Key key(branch);
577 B3::CheckSpecial* special = static_cast<B3::CheckSpecial*>(m_code.addSpecial(makeUnique<B3::CheckSpecial>(key)));
578
579 // FIXME: Remove the need for dummy values
580 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=194040
581 B3::Value* dummyPredicate = m_proc.addConstant(B3::Origin(), B3::Int32, 42);
582 B3::CheckValue* checkValue = m_proc.add<B3::CheckValue>(B3::Check, B3::Origin(), dummyPredicate);
583 checkValue->setGenerator(generator);
584
585 Inst inst(Patch, checkValue, Arg::special(special));
586 inst.args.appendVector(branch.args);
587 m_currentBlock->append(WTFMove(inst));
588 }
589
590 template <typename Func, typename ...Args>
591 void emitCCall(Func func, TypedTmp result, Args... args)
592 {
593 emitCCall(m_currentBlock, func, result, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
594 }
595 template <typename Func, typename ...Args>
596 void emitCCall(BasicBlock* block, Func func, TypedTmp result, Args... theArgs)
597 {
598 B3::Type resultType = B3::Void;
599 if (result) {
600 switch (result.type().kind) {
601 case TypeKind::I32:
602 resultType = B3::Int32;
603 break;
604 case TypeKind::I64:
605 case TypeKind::Externref:
606 case TypeKind::Funcref:
607 case TypeKind::TypeIdx:
608 resultType = B3::Int64;
609 break;
610 case TypeKind::F32:
611 resultType = B3::Float;
612 break;
613 case TypeKind::F64:
614 resultType = B3::Double;
615 break;
616 default:
617 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
618 }
619 }
620
621 auto makeDummyValue = [&] (Tmp tmp) {
622 // FIXME: This is less than ideal to create dummy values just to satisfy Air's
623 // validation. We should abstrcat CCall enough so we're not reliant on arguments
624 // to the B3::CCallValue.
625 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=194040
626 if (tmp.isGP())
627 return m_proc.addConstant(B3::Origin(), B3::Int64, 0);
628 return m_proc.addConstant(B3::Origin(), B3::Double, 0);
629 };
630
631 B3::Value* dummyFunc = m_proc.addConstant(B3::Origin(), B3::Int64, bitwise_cast<uintptr_t>(func));
632 B3::Value* origin = m_proc.add<B3::CCallValue>(resultType, B3::Origin(), B3::Effects::none(), dummyFunc, makeDummyValue(theArgs)...);
633
634 Inst inst(CCall, origin);
635
636 Tmp callee = g64();
637 append(block, Move, Arg::immPtr(tagCFunctionPtr<void*, OperationPtrTag>(func)), callee);
638 inst.args.append(callee);
639
640 if (result)
641 inst.args.append(result.tmp());
642
643 for (Tmp tmp : Vector<Tmp, sizeof...(Args)>::from(theArgs.tmp()...))
644 inst.args.append(tmp);
645
646 block->append(WTFMove(inst));
647 }
648
649 static B3::Air::Opcode moveOpForValueType(Type type)
650 {
651 switch (type.kind) {
652 case TypeKind::I32:
653 return Move32;
654 case TypeKind::I64:
655 case TypeKind::Externref:
656 case TypeKind::Funcref:
657 case TypeKind::TypeIdx:
658 return Move;
659 case TypeKind::F32:
660 return MoveFloat;
661 case TypeKind::F64:
662 return MoveDouble;
663 default:
664 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
665 }
666 }

755// Memory accesses in WebAssembly have unsigned 32-bit offsets, whereas they have signed 32-bit offsets in B3.
756int32_t AirIRGenerator::fixupPointerPlusOffset(ExpressionType& ptr, uint32_t offset)
757{
758 if (static_cast<uint64_t>(offset) > static_cast<uint64_t>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max())) {
759 auto previousPtr = ptr;
760 ptr = g64();
761 auto constant = g64();
762 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(offset), constant);
763 append(Add64, constant, previousPtr, ptr);
764 return 0;
765 }
766 return offset;
767}
768
769void AirIRGenerator::restoreWasmContextInstance(BasicBlock* block, TypedTmp instance)
770{
771 if (Context::useFastTLS()) {
772 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
773 if (CCallHelpers::storeWasmContextInstanceNeedsMacroScratchRegister())
774 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
775 patchpoint->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
776 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsageIf allowScratch(jit, CCallHelpers::storeWasmContextInstanceNeedsMacroScratchRegister());
777 jit.storeWasmContextInstance(params[0].gpr());
778 });
779 emitPatchpoint(block, patchpoint, Tmp(), instance);
780 return;
781 }
782
783 // FIXME: Because WasmToWasm call clobbers wasmContextInstance register and does not restore it, we need to restore it in the caller side.
784 // This prevents us from using ArgumentReg to this (logically) immutable pinned register.
785 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
786 B3::Effects effects = B3::Effects::none();
787 effects.writesPinned = true;
788 effects.reads = B3::HeapRange::top();
789 patchpoint->effects = effects;
790 patchpoint->clobberLate(RegisterSet(m_wasmContextInstanceGPR));
791 GPRReg wasmContextInstanceGPR = m_wasmContextInstanceGPR;
792 patchpoint->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& param) {
793 jit.move(param[0].gpr(), wasmContextInstanceGPR);
794 });
795 emitPatchpoint(block, patchpoint, Tmp(), instance);
796}
797
798AirIRGenerator::AirIRGenerator(const ModuleInformation& info, B3::Procedure& procedure, InternalFunction* compilation, Vector<UnlinkedWasmToWasmCall>& unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls, MemoryMode mode, unsigned functionIndex, TierUpCount* tierUp, const Signature& signature)
799 : m_info(info)
800 , m_mode(mode)
801 , m_functionIndex(functionIndex)
802 , m_tierUp(tierUp)
803 , m_proc(procedure)
804 , m_code(m_proc.code())
805 , m_unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls(unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls)
806 , m_numImportFunctions(info.importFunctionCount())
807{
808 m_currentBlock = m_code.addBlock();
809 m_rootBlock = m_currentBlock;
810
811 // FIXME we don't really need to pin registers here if there's no memory. It makes wasm -> wasm thunks simpler for now. https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=166623
812 const PinnedRegisterInfo& pinnedRegs = PinnedRegisterInfo::get();
813
814 m_memoryBaseGPR = pinnedRegs.baseMemoryPointer;
815 m_code.pinRegister(m_memoryBaseGPR);
816
817 m_wasmContextInstanceGPR = pinnedRegs.wasmContextInstancePointer;
818 if (!Context::useFastTLS())
819 m_code.pinRegister(m_wasmContextInstanceGPR);
820
821 if (mode != MemoryMode::Signaling) {
822 m_boundsCheckingSizeGPR = pinnedRegs.boundsCheckingSizeRegister;
823 m_code.pinRegister(m_boundsCheckingSizeGPR);
824 }
825
826 m_code.setNumEntrypoints(1);
827
828 GPRReg contextInstance = Context::useFastTLS() ? wasmCallingConvention().prologueScratchGPRs[1] : m_wasmContextInstanceGPR;
829
830 Ref<B3::Air::PrologueGenerator> prologueGenerator = createSharedTask<B3::Air::PrologueGeneratorFunction>([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, B3::Air::Code& code) {
831 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
832 code.emitDefaultPrologue(jit);
833
834 {
835 GPRReg calleeGPR = wasmCallingConvention().prologueScratchGPRs[0];
836 auto moveLocation = jit.moveWithPatch(MacroAssembler::TrustedImmPtr(nullptr), calleeGPR);
837 jit.addLinkTask([compilation, moveLocation] (LinkBuffer& linkBuffer) {
838 compilation->calleeMoveLocation = linkBuffer.locationOf<WasmEntryPtrTag>(moveLocation);
839 });
840 jit.emitPutToCallFrameHeader(calleeGPR, CallFrameSlot::callee);
841 jit.emitPutToCallFrameHeader(nullptr, CallFrameSlot::codeBlock);
842 }
843
844 {
845 const Checked<int32_t> wasmFrameSize = m_code.frameSize();
846 const unsigned minimumParentCheckSize = WTF::roundUpToMultipleOf(stackAlignmentBytes(), 1024);
847 const unsigned extraFrameSize = WTF::roundUpToMultipleOf(stackAlignmentBytes(), std::max<uint32_t>(
848 // This allows us to elide stack checks for functions that are terminal nodes in the call
849 // tree, (e.g they don't make any calls) and have a small enough frame size. This works by
850 // having any such terminal node have its parent caller include some extra size in its
851 // own check for it. The goal here is twofold:
852 // 1. Emit less code.
853 // 2. Try to speed things up by skipping stack checks.
854 minimumParentCheckSize,
855 // This allows us to elide stack checks in the Wasm -> Embedder call IC stub. Since these will
856 // spill all arguments to the stack, we ensure that a stack check here covers the
857 // stack that such a stub would use.
858 Checked<uint32_t>(m_maxNumJSCallArguments) * sizeof(Register) + jsCallingConvention().headerSizeInBytes
859 ));
860 const int32_t checkSize = m_makesCalls ? (wasmFrameSize + extraFrameSize).value() : wasmFrameSize.value();
861 bool needUnderflowCheck = static_cast<unsigned>(checkSize) > Options::reservedZoneSize();
862 bool needsOverflowCheck = m_makesCalls || wasmFrameSize >= static_cast<int32_t>(minimumParentCheckSize) || needUnderflowCheck;
863
864 // This allows leaf functions to not do stack checks if their frame size is within
865 // certain limits since their caller would have already done the check.
866 if (needsOverflowCheck) {
867 GPRReg scratch = wasmCallingConvention().prologueScratchGPRs[0];
868
869 if (Context::useFastTLS())
870 jit.loadWasmContextInstance(contextInstance);
871
872 jit.addPtr(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(-checkSize), GPRInfo::callFrameRegister, scratch);
873 MacroAssembler::JumpList overflow;
874 if (UNLIKELY(needUnderflowCheck))
875 overflow.append(jit.branchPtr(CCallHelpers::Above, scratch, GPRInfo::callFrameRegister));
876 overflow.append(jit.branchPtr(CCallHelpers::Below, scratch, CCallHelpers::Address(contextInstance, Instance::offsetOfCachedStackLimit())));
877 jit.addLinkTask([overflow] (LinkBuffer& linkBuffer) {
878 linkBuffer.link(overflow, CodeLocationLabel<JITThunkPtrTag>(Thunks::singleton().stub(throwStackOverflowFromWasmThunkGenerator).code()));
879 });
880 } else if (m_usesInstanceValue && Context::useFastTLS()) {
881 // No overflow check is needed, but the instance values still needs to be correct.
882 jit.loadWasmContextInstance(contextInstance);
883 }
884 }
885 });
886
887 m_code.setPrologueForEntrypoint(0, WTFMove(prologueGenerator));
888
889 if (Context::useFastTLS()) {
890 m_instanceValue = g64();
891 // FIXME: Would be nice to only do this if we use instance value.
892 append(Move, Tmp(contextInstance), m_instanceValue);
893 } else
894 m_instanceValue = { Tmp(contextInstance), Types::I64 };
895
896 ASSERT(!m_locals.size());
897 m_locals.grow(signature.argumentCount());
898 for (unsigned i = 0; i < signature.argumentCount(); ++i) {
899 Type type = signature.argument(i);
900 m_locals[i] = tmpForType(type);
901 }
902
903 CallInformation wasmCallInfo = wasmCallingConvention().callInformationFor(signature, CallRole::Callee);
904
905 for (unsigned i = 0; i < wasmCallInfo.params.size(); ++i) {
906 B3::ValueRep location = wasmCallInfo.params[i];
907 Arg arg = location.isReg() ? Arg(Tmp(location.reg())) : Arg::addr(Tmp(GPRInfo::callFrameRegister), location.offsetFromFP());
908 switch (signature.argument(i).kind) {
909 case TypeKind::I32:
910 append(Move32, arg, m_locals[i]);
911 break;
912 case TypeKind::I64:
913 case TypeKind::Externref:
914 case TypeKind::Funcref:
915 case TypeKind::TypeIdx:
916 append(Move, arg, m_locals[i]);
917 break;
918 case TypeKind::F32:
919 append(MoveFloat, arg, m_locals[i]);
920 break;
921 case TypeKind::F64:
922 append(MoveDouble, arg, m_locals[i]);
923 break;
924 default:
925 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
926 }
927 }
928
929 emitEntryTierUpCheck();
930}
931
932B3::Type AirIRGenerator::toB3ResultType(BlockSignature returnType)
933{
934 if (returnType->returnsVoid())
935 return B3::Void;
936
937 if (returnType->returnCount() == 1)
938 return toB3Type(returnType->returnType(0));
939
940 auto result = m_tupleMap.ensure(returnType, [&] {
941 Vector<B3::Type> result;
942 for (unsigned i = 0; i < returnType->returnCount(); ++i)
943 result.append(toB3Type(returnType->returnType(i)));
944 return m_proc.addTuple(WTFMove(result));
945 });
946 return result.iterator->value;
947}
948
949void AirIRGenerator::restoreWebAssemblyGlobalState(RestoreCachedStackLimit restoreCachedStackLimit, const MemoryInformation& memory, TypedTmp instance, BasicBlock* block)
950{
951 restoreWasmContextInstance(block, instance);
952
953 if (restoreCachedStackLimit == RestoreCachedStackLimit::Yes) {
954 // The Instance caches the stack limit, but also knows where its canonical location is.
955 static_assert(sizeof(std::declval<Instance*>()->cachedStackLimit()) == sizeof(uint64_t), "codegen relies on this size");
956
957 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(Instance::offsetOfPointerToActualStackLimit(), B3::Width64));
958 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(Instance::offsetOfCachedStackLimit(), B3::Width64));
959 auto temp = g64();
960 append(block, Move, Arg::addr(instanceValue(), Instance::offsetOfPointerToActualStackLimit()), temp);
961 append(block, Move, Arg::addr(temp), temp);
962 append(block, Move, temp, Arg::addr(instanceValue(), Instance::offsetOfCachedStackLimit()));
963 }
964
965 if (!!memory) {
966 const PinnedRegisterInfo* pinnedRegs = &PinnedRegisterInfo::get();
967 RegisterSet clobbers;
968 clobbers.set(pinnedRegs->baseMemoryPointer);
969 clobbers.set(pinnedRegs->boundsCheckingSizeRegister);
970 clobbers.set(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
971
972 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
973 B3::Effects effects = B3::Effects::none();
974 effects.writesPinned = true;
975 effects.reads = B3::HeapRange::top();
976 patchpoint->effects = effects;
977 patchpoint->clobber(clobbers);
978 patchpoint->numGPScratchRegisters = 1;
979
980 patchpoint->setGenerator([pinnedRegs] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
981 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
982 GPRReg baseMemory = pinnedRegs->baseMemoryPointer;
983 GPRReg scratch = params.gpScratch(0);
984
985 jit.loadPtr(CCallHelpers::Address(params[0].gpr(), Instance::offsetOfCachedBoundsCheckingSize()), pinnedRegs->boundsCheckingSizeRegister);
986 jit.loadPtr(CCallHelpers::Address(params[0].gpr(), Instance::offsetOfCachedMemory()), baseMemory);
987
988 jit.cageConditionallyAndUntag(Gigacage::Primitive, baseMemory, pinnedRegs->boundsCheckingSizeRegister, scratch);
989 });
990
991 emitPatchpoint(block, patchpoint, Tmp(), instance);
992 }
993}
994
995void AirIRGenerator::emitThrowException(CCallHelpers& jit, ExceptionType type)
996{
997 jit.move(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(static_cast<uint32_t>(type)), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
998 auto jumpToExceptionStub = jit.jump();
999
1000 jit.addLinkTask([jumpToExceptionStub] (LinkBuffer& linkBuffer) {
1001 linkBuffer.link(jumpToExceptionStub, CodeLocationLabel<JITThunkPtrTag>(Thunks::singleton().stub(throwExceptionFromWasmThunkGenerator).code()));
1002 });
1003}
1004
1005auto AirIRGenerator::addLocal(Type type, uint32_t count) -> PartialResult
1006{
1007 size_t newSize = m_locals.size() + count;
1008 ASSERT(!(CheckedUint32(count) + m_locals.size()).hasOverflowed());
1009 ASSERT(newSize <= maxFunctionLocals);
1010 WASM_COMPILE_FAIL_IF(!m_locals.tryReserveCapacity(newSize), "can't allocate memory for ", newSize, " locals");
1011
1012 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
1013 auto local = tmpForType(type);
1014 m_locals.uncheckedAppend(local);
1015 switch (type.kind) {
1016 case TypeKind::Externref:
1017 case TypeKind::Funcref:
1018 case TypeKind::TypeIdx:
1019 append(Move, Arg::imm(JSValue::encode(jsNull())), local);
1020 break;
1021 case TypeKind::I32:
1022 case TypeKind::I64: {
1023 append(Xor64, local, local);
1024 break;
1025 }
1026 case TypeKind::F32:
1027 case TypeKind::F64: {
1028 auto temp = g64();
1029 // IEEE 754 "0" is just int32/64 zero.
1030 append(Xor64, temp, temp);
1031 append(type.isF32() ? Move32ToFloat : Move64ToDouble, temp, local);
1032 break;
1033 }
1034 default:
1035 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1036 }
1037 }
1038 return { };
1039}
1040
1041auto AirIRGenerator::addConstant(Type type, uint64_t value) -> ExpressionType
1042{
1043 return addConstant(m_currentBlock, type, value);
1044}
1045
1046auto AirIRGenerator::addConstant(BasicBlock* block, Type type, uint64_t value) -> ExpressionType
1047{
1048 auto result = tmpForType(type);
1049 switch (type.kind) {
1050 case TypeKind::I32:
1051 case TypeKind::I64:
1052 case TypeKind::Externref:
1053 case TypeKind::Funcref:
1054 case TypeKind::TypeIdx:
1055 append(block, Move, Arg::bigImm(value), result);
1056 break;
1057 case TypeKind::F32:
1058 case TypeKind::F64: {
1059 auto tmp = g64();
1060 append(block, Move, Arg::bigImm(value), tmp);
1061 append(block, type.isF32() ? Move32ToFloat : Move64ToDouble, tmp, result);
1062 break;
1063 }
1064
1065 default:
1066 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1067 }
1068
1069 return result;
1070}

1188
1189auto AirIRGenerator::addTableGrow(unsigned tableIndex, ExpressionType fill, ExpressionType delta, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
1190{
1191 ASSERT(fill.tmp());
1192 ASSERT(isSubtype(fill.type(), m_info.tables[tableIndex].wasmType()));
1193 ASSERT(delta.tmp());
1194 ASSERT(delta.type().isI32());
1195 result = tmpForType(Types::I32);
1196
1197 emitCCall(&operationWasmTableGrow, result, instanceValue(), addConstant(Types::I32, tableIndex), fill, delta);
1198
1199 return { };
1200}

1277
1278auto AirIRGenerator::addCurrentMemory(ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
1279{
1280 static_assert(sizeof(std::declval<Memory*>()->size()) == sizeof(uint64_t), "codegen relies on this size");
1281
1282 auto temp1 = g64();
1283 auto temp2 = g64();
1284
1285 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(Instance::offsetOfMemory(), B3::Width64));
1286 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(Memory::offsetOfHandle(), B3::Width64));
1287 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(MemoryHandle::offsetOfSize(), B3::Width64));
1288 append(Move, Arg::addr(instanceValue(), Instance::offsetOfMemory()), temp1);
1289 append(Move, Arg::addr(temp1, Memory::offsetOfHandle()), temp1);
1290 append(Move, Arg::addr(temp1, MemoryHandle::offsetOfSize()), temp1);
1291 constexpr uint32_t shiftValue = 16;
1292 static_assert(PageCount::pageSize == 1ull << shiftValue, "This must hold for the code below to be correct.");
1293 append(Move, Arg::imm(16), temp2);
1294 addShift(Types::I32, Urshift64, temp1, temp2, result);
1295 append(Move32, result, result);
1296
1297 return { };
1298}

1388
1389auto AirIRGenerator::getGlobal(uint32_t index, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
1390{
1391 const Wasm::GlobalInformation& global = m_info.globals[index];
1392 Type type = global.type;
1393
1394 result = tmpForType(type);
1395
1396 auto temp = g64();
1397
1398 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(Instance::offsetOfGlobals(), B3::Width64));
1399 append(Move, Arg::addr(instanceValue(), Instance::offsetOfGlobals()), temp);
1400
1401 int32_t offset = safeCast<int32_t>(index * sizeof(Register));
1402 switch (global.bindingMode) {
1403 case Wasm::GlobalInformation::BindingMode::EmbeddedInInstance:
1404 if (Arg::isValidAddrForm(offset, B3::widthForType(toB3Type(type))))
1405 append(moveOpForValueType(type), Arg::addr(temp, offset), result);
1406 else {
1407 auto temp2 = g64();
1408 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(offset), temp2);
1409 append(Add64, temp2, temp, temp);
1410 append(moveOpForValueType(type), Arg::addr(temp), result);
1411 }
1412 break;
1413 case Wasm::GlobalInformation::BindingMode::Portable:
1414 ASSERT(global.mutability == Wasm::GlobalInformation::Mutability::Mutable);
1415 if (Arg::isValidAddrForm(offset, B3::Width64))
1416 append(Move, Arg::addr(temp, offset), temp);
1417 else {
1418 auto temp2 = g64();
1419 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(offset), temp2);
1420 append(Add64, temp2, temp, temp);
1421 append(Move, Arg::addr(temp), temp);
1422 }
1423 append(moveOpForValueType(type), Arg::addr(temp), result);
1424 break;
1425 }
1426 return { };
1427}
1428
1429auto AirIRGenerator::setGlobal(uint32_t index, ExpressionType value) -> PartialResult
1430{
1431 auto temp = g64();
1432
1433 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(Instance::offsetOfGlobals(), B3::Width64));
1434 append(Move, Arg::addr(instanceValue(), Instance::offsetOfGlobals()), temp);
1435
1436 const Wasm::GlobalInformation& global = m_info.globals[index];
1437 Type type = global.type;
1438
1439 int32_t offset = safeCast<int32_t>(index * sizeof(Register));
1440 switch (global.bindingMode) {
1441 case Wasm::GlobalInformation::BindingMode::EmbeddedInInstance:
1442 if (Arg::isValidAddrForm(offset, B3::widthForType(toB3Type(type))))
1443 append(moveOpForValueType(type), value, Arg::addr(temp, offset));
1444 else {
1445 auto temp2 = g64();
1446 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(offset), temp2);
1447 append(Add64, temp2, temp, temp);
1448 append(moveOpForValueType(type), value, Arg::addr(temp));
1449 }
1450 if (isRefType(type))
1451 emitWriteBarrierForJSWrapper();
1452 break;
1453 case Wasm::GlobalInformation::BindingMode::Portable:
1454 ASSERT(global.mutability == Wasm::GlobalInformation::Mutability::Mutable);
1455 if (Arg::isValidAddrForm(offset, B3::Width64))
1456 append(Move, Arg::addr(temp, offset), temp);
1457 else {
1458 auto temp2 = g64();
1459 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(offset), temp2);
1460 append(Add64, temp2, temp, temp);
1461 append(Move, Arg::addr(temp), temp);
1462 }
1463 append(moveOpForValueType(type), value, Arg::addr(temp));
1464 // We emit a write-barrier onto JSWebAssemblyGlobal, not JSWebAssemblyInstance.
1465 if (isRefType(type)) {
1466 auto cell = g64();
1467 auto vm = g64();
1468 auto cellState = g32();
1469 auto threshold = g32();
1470
1471 BasicBlock* fenceCheckPath = m_code.addBlock();
1472 BasicBlock* fencePath = m_code.addBlock();
1473 BasicBlock* doSlowPath = m_code.addBlock();
1474 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
1475
1476 append(Move, Arg::addr(instanceValue(), Instance::offsetOfOwner()), cell);
1477 append(Move, Arg::addr(cell, JSWebAssemblyInstance::offsetOfVM()), vm);
1478
1479 append(Move, Arg::addr(temp, Wasm::Global::offsetOfOwner() - Wasm::Global::offsetOfValue()), cell);
1480 append(Load8, Arg::addr(cell, JSCell::cellStateOffset()), cellState);
1481 append(Move32, Arg::addr(vm, VM::offsetOfHeapBarrierThreshold()), threshold);
1482
1483 append(Branch32, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::Above), cellState, threshold);
1484 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(continuation, fenceCheckPath);
1485 m_currentBlock = fenceCheckPath;
1486
1487 append(Load8, Arg::addr(vm, VM::offsetOfHeapMutatorShouldBeFenced()), threshold);
1488 append(BranchTest32, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::Zero), threshold, threshold);
1489 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(doSlowPath, fencePath);
1490 m_currentBlock = fencePath;
1491
1492 auto* doFence = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
1493 doFence->setGenerator([] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
1494 jit.memoryFence();
1495 });
1496 emitPatchpoint(doFence, Tmp());
1497
1498 append(Load8, Arg::addr(cell, JSCell::cellStateOffset()), cellState);
1499 append(Branch32, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::Above), cellState, Arg::imm(blackThreshold));
1500 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(continuation, doSlowPath);
1501 m_currentBlock = doSlowPath;
1502
1503 emitCCall(&operationWasmWriteBarrierSlowPath, TypedTmp(), cell, vm);
1504 append(Jump);
1505 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(continuation);
1506 m_currentBlock = continuation;
1507 }
1508 break;
1509 }
1510
1511 return { };
1512}
1513
1514inline void AirIRGenerator::emitWriteBarrierForJSWrapper()
1515{
1516 auto cell = g64();
1517 auto vm = g64();
1518 auto cellState = g32();
1519 auto threshold = g32();
1520
1521 BasicBlock* fenceCheckPath = m_code.addBlock();
1522 BasicBlock* fencePath = m_code.addBlock();
1523 BasicBlock* doSlowPath = m_code.addBlock();
1524 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
1525
1526 append(Move, Arg::addr(instanceValue(), Instance::offsetOfOwner()), cell);
1527 append(Move, Arg::addr(cell, JSWebAssemblyInstance::offsetOfVM()), vm);
1528 append(Load8, Arg::addr(cell, JSCell::cellStateOffset()), cellState);
1529 append(Move32, Arg::addr(vm, VM::offsetOfHeapBarrierThreshold()), threshold);
1530
1531 append(Branch32, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::Above), cellState, threshold);
1532 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(continuation, fenceCheckPath);
1533 m_currentBlock = fenceCheckPath;
1534
1535 append(Load8, Arg::addr(vm, VM::offsetOfHeapMutatorShouldBeFenced()), threshold);
1536 append(BranchTest32, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::Zero), threshold, threshold);
1537 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(doSlowPath, fencePath);
1538 m_currentBlock = fencePath;
1539
1540 auto* doFence = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
1541 doFence->setGenerator([] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
1542 jit.memoryFence();
1543 });
1544 emitPatchpoint(doFence, Tmp());
1545
1546 append(Load8, Arg::addr(cell, JSCell::cellStateOffset()), cellState);
1547 append(Branch32, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::Above), cellState, Arg::imm(blackThreshold));
1548 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(continuation, doSlowPath);
1549 m_currentBlock = doSlowPath;
1550
1551 emitCCall(&operationWasmWriteBarrierSlowPath, TypedTmp(), cell, vm);
1552 append(Jump);
1553 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(continuation);
1554 m_currentBlock = continuation;
1555}
1556
1557inline AirIRGenerator::ExpressionType AirIRGenerator::emitCheckAndPreparePointer(ExpressionType pointer, uint32_t offset, uint32_t sizeOfOperation)
1558{
1559 ASSERT(m_memoryBaseGPR);
1560
1561 auto result = g64();
1562 append(Move32, pointer, result);
1563
1564 switch (m_mode) {
1565 case MemoryMode::BoundsChecking: {
1566 // In bound checking mode, while shared wasm memory partially relies on signal handler too, we need to perform bound checking
1567 // to ensure that no memory access exceeds the current memory size.
1568 ASSERT(m_boundsCheckingSizeGPR);
1569 ASSERT(sizeOfOperation + offset > offset);
1570 auto temp = g64();
1571 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(static_cast<uint64_t>(sizeOfOperation) + offset - 1), temp);
1572 append(Add64, result, temp);
1573
1574 emitCheck([&] {
1575 return Inst(Branch64, nullptr, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::AboveOrEqual), temp, Tmp(m_boundsCheckingSizeGPR));
1576 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
1577 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
1578 });
1579 break;
1580 }
1581
1582 case MemoryMode::Signaling: {
1583 // We've virtually mapped 4GiB+redzone for this memory. Only the user-allocated pages are addressable, contiguously in range [0, current],
1584 // and everything above is mapped PROT_NONE. We don't need to perform any explicit bounds check in the 4GiB range because WebAssembly register
1585 // memory accesses are 32-bit. However WebAssembly register + offset accesses perform the addition in 64-bit which can push an access above
1586 // the 32-bit limit (the offset is unsigned 32-bit). The redzone will catch most small offsets, and we'll explicitly bounds check any
1587 // register + large offset access. We don't think this will be generated frequently.
1588 //
1589 // We could check that register + large offset doesn't exceed 4GiB+redzone since that's technically the limit we need to avoid overflowing the
1590 // PROT_NONE region, but it's better if we use a smaller immediate because it can codegens better. We know that anything equal to or greater
1591 // than the declared 'maximum' will trap, so we can compare against that number. If there was no declared 'maximum' then we still know that
1592 // any access equal to or greater than 4GiB will trap, no need to add the redzone.
1593 if (offset >= Memory::fastMappedRedzoneBytes()) {
1594 uint64_t maximum = m_info.memory.maximum() ? m_info.memory.maximum().bytes() : std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max();
1595 auto temp = g64();
1596 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(static_cast<uint64_t>(sizeOfOperation) + offset - 1), temp);
1597 append(Add64, result, temp);
1598 auto sizeMax = addConstant(Types::I64, maximum);
1599
1600 emitCheck([&] {
1601 return Inst(Branch64, nullptr, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::AboveOrEqual), temp, sizeMax);
1602 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
1603 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
1604 });
1605 }
1606 break;
1607 }
1608 }
1609
1610 append(Add64, Tmp(m_memoryBaseGPR), result);
1611 return result;
1612}
1613
1614inline uint32_t sizeOfLoadOp(LoadOpType op)
1615{
1616 switch (op) {
1617 case LoadOpType::I32Load8S:
1618 case LoadOpType::I32Load8U:
1619 case LoadOpType::I64Load8S:
1620 case LoadOpType::I64Load8U:
1621 return 1;
1622 case LoadOpType::I32Load16S:
1623 case LoadOpType::I64Load16S:
1624 case LoadOpType::I32Load16U:
1625 case LoadOpType::I64Load16U:
1626 return 2;
1627 case LoadOpType::I32Load:
1628 case LoadOpType::I64Load32S:
1629 case LoadOpType::I64Load32U:
1630 case LoadOpType::F32Load:
1631 return 4;
1632 case LoadOpType::I64Load:
1633 case LoadOpType::F64Load:
1634 return 8;
1635 }
1636 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1637}
1638
1639inline TypedTmp AirIRGenerator::emitLoadOp(LoadOpType op, ExpressionType pointer, uint32_t uoffset)
1640{
1641 uint32_t offset = fixupPointerPlusOffset(pointer, uoffset);
1642
1643 TypedTmp immTmp;
1644 TypedTmp newPtr;
1645 TypedTmp result;
1646
1647 Arg addrArg;
1648 if (Arg::isValidAddrForm(offset, B3::widthForBytes(sizeOfLoadOp(op))))
1649 addrArg = Arg::addr(pointer, offset);
1650 else {
1651 immTmp = g64();
1652 newPtr = g64();
1653 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(offset), immTmp);
1654 append(Add64, immTmp, pointer, newPtr);
1655 addrArg = Arg::addr(newPtr);
1656 }
1657
1658 switch (op) {
1659 case LoadOpType::I32Load8S: {
1660 result = g32();
1661 appendEffectful(Load8SignedExtendTo32, addrArg, result);
1662 break;
1663 }
1664
1665 case LoadOpType::I64Load8S: {
1666 result = g64();
1667 appendEffectful(Load8SignedExtendTo32, addrArg, result);
1668 append(SignExtend32ToPtr, result, result);
1669 break;
1670 }
1671
1672 case LoadOpType::I32Load8U: {
1673 result = g32();
1674 appendEffectful(Load8, addrArg, result);
1675 break;
1676 }
1677
1678 case LoadOpType::I64Load8U: {
1679 result = g64();
1680 appendEffectful(Load8, addrArg, result);
1681 break;
1682 }
1683
1684 case LoadOpType::I32Load16S: {
1685 result = g32();
1686 appendEffectful(Load16SignedExtendTo32, addrArg, result);
1687 break;
1688 }
1689
1690 case LoadOpType::I64Load16S: {
1691 result = g64();
1692 appendEffectful(Load16SignedExtendTo32, addrArg, result);
1693 append(SignExtend32ToPtr, result, result);
1694 break;
1695 }
1696
1697 case LoadOpType::I32Load16U: {
1698 result = g32();
1699 appendEffectful(Load16, addrArg, result);
1700 break;
1701 }
1702
1703 case LoadOpType::I64Load16U: {
1704 result = g64();
1705 appendEffectful(Load16, addrArg, result);
1706 break;
1707 }
1708
1709 case LoadOpType::I32Load:
1710 result = g32();
1711 appendEffectful(Move32, addrArg, result);
1712 break;
1713
1714 case LoadOpType::I64Load32U: {
1715 result = g64();
1716 appendEffectful(Move32, addrArg, result);
1717 break;
1718 }
1719
1720 case LoadOpType::I64Load32S: {
1721 result = g64();
1722 appendEffectful(Move32, addrArg, result);
1723 append(SignExtend32ToPtr, result, result);
1724 break;
1725 }
1726
1727 case LoadOpType::I64Load: {
1728 result = g64();
1729 appendEffectful(Move, addrArg, result);
1730 break;
1731 }
1732
1733 case LoadOpType::F32Load: {
1734 result = f32();
1735 appendEffectful(MoveFloat, addrArg, result);
1736 break;
1737 }
1738
1739 case LoadOpType::F64Load: {
1740 result = f64();
1741 appendEffectful(MoveDouble, addrArg, result);
1742 break;
1743 }
1744 }
1745
1746 return result;
1747}
1748
1749auto AirIRGenerator::load(LoadOpType op, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType& result, uint32_t offset) -> PartialResult
1750{
1751 ASSERT(pointer.tmp().isGP());
1752
1753 if (UNLIKELY(sumOverflows<uint32_t>(offset, sizeOfLoadOp(op)))) {
1754 // FIXME: Even though this is provably out of bounds, it's not a validation error, so we have to handle it
1755 // as a runtime exception. However, this may change: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=166435
1756 auto* patch = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
1757 patch->setGenerator([this] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
1758 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
1759 });
1760 emitPatchpoint(patch, Tmp());
1761
1762 // We won't reach here, so we just pick a random reg.
1763 switch (op) {
1764 case LoadOpType::I32Load8S:
1765 case LoadOpType::I32Load16S:
1766 case LoadOpType::I32Load:
1767 case LoadOpType::I32Load16U:
1768 case LoadOpType::I32Load8U:
1769 result = g32();
1770 break;
1771 case LoadOpType::I64Load8S:
1772 case LoadOpType::I64Load8U:
1773 case LoadOpType::I64Load16S:
1774 case LoadOpType::I64Load32U:
1775 case LoadOpType::I64Load32S:
1776 case LoadOpType::I64Load:
1777 case LoadOpType::I64Load16U:
1778 result = g64();
1779 break;
1780 case LoadOpType::F32Load:
1781 result = f32();
1782 break;
1783 case LoadOpType::F64Load:
1784 result = f64();
1785 break;
1786 }
1787 } else
1788 result = emitLoadOp(op, emitCheckAndPreparePointer(pointer, offset, sizeOfLoadOp(op)), offset);
1789
1790 return { };
1791}
1792
1793inline uint32_t sizeOfStoreOp(StoreOpType op)
1794{
1795 switch (op) {
1796 case StoreOpType::I32Store8:
1797 case StoreOpType::I64Store8:
1798 return 1;
1799 case StoreOpType::I32Store16:
1800 case StoreOpType::I64Store16:
1801 return 2;
1802 case StoreOpType::I32Store:
1803 case StoreOpType::I64Store32:
1804 case StoreOpType::F32Store:
1805 return 4;
1806 case StoreOpType::I64Store:
1807 case StoreOpType::F64Store:
1808 return 8;
1809 }
1810 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1811}
1812
1813
1814inline void AirIRGenerator::emitStoreOp(StoreOpType op, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType value, uint32_t uoffset)
1815{
1816 uint32_t offset = fixupPointerPlusOffset(pointer, uoffset);
1817
1818 TypedTmp immTmp;
1819 TypedTmp newPtr;
1820
1821 Arg addrArg;
1822 if (Arg::isValidAddrForm(offset, B3::widthForBytes(sizeOfStoreOp(op))))
1823 addrArg = Arg::addr(pointer, offset);
1824 else {
1825 immTmp = g64();
1826 newPtr = g64();
1827 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(offset), immTmp);
1828 append(Add64, immTmp, pointer, newPtr);
1829 addrArg = Arg::addr(newPtr);
1830 }
1831
1832 switch (op) {
1833 case StoreOpType::I64Store8:
1834 case StoreOpType::I32Store8:
1835 append(Store8, value, addrArg);
1836 return;
1837
1838 case StoreOpType::I64Store16:
1839 case StoreOpType::I32Store16:
1840 append(Store16, value, addrArg);
1841 return;
1842
1843 case StoreOpType::I64Store32:
1844 case StoreOpType::I32Store:
1845 append(Move32, value, addrArg);
1846 return;
1847
1848 case StoreOpType::I64Store:
1849 append(Move, value, addrArg);
1850 return;
1851
1852 case StoreOpType::F32Store:
1853 append(MoveFloat, value, addrArg);
1854 return;
1855
1856 case StoreOpType::F64Store:
1857 append(MoveDouble, value, addrArg);
1858 return;
1859 }
1860
1861 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1862}
1863
1864auto AirIRGenerator::store(StoreOpType op, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType value, uint32_t offset) -> PartialResult
1865{
1866 ASSERT(pointer.tmp().isGP());
1867
1868 if (UNLIKELY(sumOverflows<uint32_t>(offset, sizeOfStoreOp(op)))) {
1869 // FIXME: Even though this is provably out of bounds, it's not a validation error, so we have to handle it
1870 // as a runtime exception. However, this may change: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=166435
1871 auto* throwException = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
1872 throwException->setGenerator([this] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
1873 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
1874 });
1875 emitPatchpoint(throwException, Tmp());
1876 } else
1877 emitStoreOp(op, emitCheckAndPreparePointer(pointer, offset, sizeOfStoreOp(op)), value, offset);
1878
1879 return { };
1880}
1881
1882#define OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(opcode, width) ( \
1883 (width) == B3::Width8 ? B3::Air::opcode ## 8 : \
1884 (width) == B3::Width16 ? B3::Air::opcode ## 16 : \
1885 (width) == B3::Width32 ? B3::Air::opcode ## 32 : \
1886 B3::Air::opcode ## 64)
1887#define OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(opcode, width) ( \
1888 (width) == B3::Width64 ? B3::Air::opcode ## 64 : B3::Air::opcode ## 32)
1889
1890inline B3::Width accessWidth(ExtAtomicOpType op)
1891{
1892 return static_cast<B3::Width>(memoryLog2Alignment(op));
1893}
1894
1895inline uint32_t sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(ExtAtomicOpType op)
1896{
1897 return bytesForWidth(accessWidth(op));
1898}
1899
1900auto AirIRGenerator::fixupPointerPlusOffsetForAtomicOps(ExtAtomicOpType op, ExpressionType pointer, uint32_t uoffset) -> ExpressionType
1901{
1902 uint32_t offset = fixupPointerPlusOffset(pointer, uoffset);
1903 if (Arg::isValidAddrForm(offset, B3::widthForBytes(sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op)))) {
1904 if (offset == 0)
1905 return pointer;
1906 TypedTmp newPtr = g64();
1907 append(Lea64, Arg::addr(pointer, offset), newPtr);
1908 return newPtr;
1909 }
1910 TypedTmp newPtr = g64();
1911 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(offset), newPtr);
1912 append(Add64, pointer, newPtr);
1913 return newPtr;
1914}
1915
1916void AirIRGenerator::sanitizeAtomicResult(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, Tmp source, Tmp dest)
1917{
1918 switch (valueType.kind) {
1919 case TypeKind::I64: {
1920 switch (accessWidth(op)) {
1921 case B3::Width8:
1922 append(ZeroExtend8To32, source, dest);
1923 return;
1924 case B3::Width16:
1925 append(ZeroExtend16To32, source, dest);
1926 return;
1927 case B3::Width32:
1928 append(Move32, source, dest);
1929 return;
1930 case B3::Width64:
1931 if (source == dest)
1932 return;
1933 append(Move, source, dest);
1934 return;
1935 }
1936 return;
1937 }
1938 case TypeKind::I32:
1939 switch (accessWidth(op)) {
1940 case B3::Width8:
1941 append(ZeroExtend8To32, source, dest);
1942 return;
1943 case B3::Width16:
1944 append(ZeroExtend16To32, source, dest);
1945 return;
1946 case B3::Width32:
1947 case B3::Width64:
1948 if (source == dest)
1949 return;
1950 append(Move, source, dest);
1951 return;
1952 }
1953 return;
1954 default:
1955 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1956 return;
1957 }
1958}
1959
1960void AirIRGenerator::sanitizeAtomicResult(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, Tmp result)
1961{
1962 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, result, result);
1963}
1964
1965TypedTmp AirIRGenerator::appendGeneralAtomic(ExtAtomicOpType op, B3::Air::Opcode opcode, B3::Commutativity commutativity, Arg input, Arg address, TypedTmp oldValue)
1966{
1967 B3::Width accessWidth = Wasm::accessWidth(op);
1968
1969 auto newTmp = [&]() {
1970 if (accessWidth == B3::Width64)
1971 return g64();
1972 return g32();
1973 };
1974
1975 auto tmp = [&](Arg arg) -> TypedTmp {
1976 if (arg.isTmp())
1977 return TypedTmp(arg.tmp(), accessWidth == B3::Width64 ? Types::I64 : Types::I32);
1978 TypedTmp result = newTmp();
1979 append(Move, arg, result);
1980 return result;
1981 };
1982
1983 auto imm = [&](Arg arg) {
1984 if (arg.isImm())
1985 return arg;
1986 return Arg();
1987 };
1988
1989 auto bitImm = [&](Arg arg) {
1990 if (arg.isBitImm())
1991 return arg;
1992 return Arg();
1993 };
1994
1995 Tmp newValue = opcode == B3::Air::Nop ? tmp(input) : newTmp();
1996
1997 // We need a CAS loop or a LL/SC loop. Using prepare/attempt jargon, we want:
1998 //
1999 // Block #reloop:
2000 // Prepare
2001 // opcode
2002 // Attempt
2003 // Successors: Then:#done, Else:#reloop
2004 // Block #done:
2005 // Move oldValue, result
2006
2007 auto* beginBlock = m_currentBlock;
2008 auto* reloopBlock = m_code.addBlock();
2009 auto* doneBlock = m_code.addBlock();
2010
2011 append(B3::Air::Jump);
2012 beginBlock->setSuccessors(reloopBlock);
2013 m_currentBlock = reloopBlock;
2014
2015 B3::Air::Opcode prepareOpcode;
2016 if (isX86()) {
2017 switch (accessWidth) {
2018 case B3::Width8:
2019 prepareOpcode = Load8SignedExtendTo32;
2020 break;
2021 case B3::Width16:
2022 prepareOpcode = Load16SignedExtendTo32;
2023 break;
2024 case B3::Width32:
2025 prepareOpcode = Move32;
2026 break;
2027 case B3::Width64:
2028 prepareOpcode = Move;
2029 break;
2030 }
2031 } else {
2032 RELEASE_ASSERT(isARM64());
2033 prepareOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(LoadLinkAcq, accessWidth);
2034 }
2035 appendEffectful(prepareOpcode, address, oldValue);
2036
2037 if (opcode != B3::Air::Nop) {
2038 // FIXME: If we ever have to write this again, we need to find a way to share the code with
2039 // appendBinOp.
2040 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=169249
2041 if (commutativity == B3::Commutative && imm(input) && isValidForm(opcode, Arg::Imm, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp))
2042 append(opcode, imm(input), oldValue, newValue);
2043 else if (imm(input) && isValidForm(opcode, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Imm, Arg::Tmp))
2044 append(opcode, oldValue, imm(input), newValue);
2045 else if (commutativity == B3::Commutative && bitImm(input) && isValidForm(opcode, Arg::BitImm, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp))
2046 append(opcode, bitImm(input), oldValue, newValue);
2047 else if (isValidForm(opcode, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp))
2048 append(opcode, oldValue, tmp(input), newValue);
2049 else {
2050 append(Move, oldValue, newValue);
2051 if (imm(input) && isValidForm(opcode, Arg::Imm, Arg::Tmp))
2052 append(opcode, imm(input), newValue);
2053 else
2054 append(opcode, tmp(input), newValue);
2055 }
2056 }
2057
2058 if (isX86()) {
2059#if CPU(X86) || CPU(X86_64)
2060 Tmp eax(X86Registers::eax);
2061 B3::Air::Opcode casOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(BranchAtomicStrongCAS, accessWidth);
2062 append(Move, oldValue, eax);
2063 appendEffectful(casOpcode, Arg::statusCond(MacroAssembler::Success), eax, newValue, address);
2064#endif
2065 } else {
2066 RELEASE_ASSERT(isARM64());
2067 TypedTmp boolResult = newTmp();
2068 appendEffectful(OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(StoreCondRel, accessWidth), newValue, address, boolResult);
2069 append(BranchTest32, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::Zero), boolResult, boolResult);
2070 }
2071 reloopBlock->setSuccessors(doneBlock, reloopBlock);
2072 m_currentBlock = doneBlock;
2073 return oldValue;
2074}
2075
2076TypedTmp AirIRGenerator::appendStrongCAS(ExtAtomicOpType op, TypedTmp expected, TypedTmp value, Arg address, TypedTmp valueResultTmp)
2077{
2078 B3::Width accessWidth = Wasm::accessWidth(op);
2079
2080 auto newTmp = [&]() {
2081 if (accessWidth == B3::Width64)
2082 return g64();
2083 return g32();
2084 };
2085
2086 auto tmp = [&](Arg arg) -> TypedTmp {
2087 if (arg.isTmp())
2088 return TypedTmp(arg.tmp(), accessWidth == B3::Width64 ? Types::I64 : Types::I32);
2089 TypedTmp result = newTmp();
2090 append(Move, arg, result);
2091 return result;
2092 };
2093
2094 Tmp successBoolResultTmp = newTmp();
2095
2096 Tmp expectedValueTmp = tmp(expected);
2097 Tmp newValueTmp = tmp(value);
2098
2099 if (isX86()) {
2100#if CPU(X86) || CPU(X86_64)
2101 Tmp eax(X86Registers::eax);
2102 append(Move, expectedValueTmp, eax);
2103 appendEffectful(OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicStrongCAS, accessWidth), eax, newValueTmp, address);
2104 append(Move, eax, valueResultTmp);
2105#endif
2106 return valueResultTmp;
2107 }
2108
2109 if (isARM64E()) {
2110 append(Move, expectedValueTmp, valueResultTmp);
2111 appendEffectful(OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicStrongCAS, accessWidth), valueResultTmp, newValueTmp, address);
2112 return valueResultTmp;
2113 }
2114
2115
2116 RELEASE_ASSERT(isARM64());
2117 // We wish to emit:
2118 //
2119 // Block #reloop:
2120 // LoadLink
2121 // Branch NotEqual
2122 // Successors: Then:#fail, Else: #store
2123 // Block #store:
2124 // StoreCond
2125 // Xor $1, %result <--- only if !invert
2126 // Jump
2127 // Successors: #done
2128 // Block #fail:
2129 // Move $invert, %result
2130 // Jump
2131 // Successors: #done
2132 // Block #done:
2133
2134 auto* reloopBlock = m_code.addBlock();
2135 auto* storeBlock = m_code.addBlock();
2136 auto* strongFailBlock = m_code.addBlock();
2137 auto* doneBlock = m_code.addBlock();
2138 auto* beginBlock = m_currentBlock;
2139
2140 append(B3::Air::Jump);
2141 beginBlock->setSuccessors(reloopBlock);
2142
2143 m_currentBlock = reloopBlock;
2144 appendEffectful(OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(LoadLinkAcq, accessWidth), address, valueResultTmp);
2145 append(OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(Branch, accessWidth), Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::NotEqual), valueResultTmp, expectedValueTmp);
2146 reloopBlock->setSuccessors(B3::Air::FrequentedBlock(strongFailBlock), storeBlock);
2147
2148 m_currentBlock = storeBlock;
2149 appendEffectful(OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(StoreCondRel, accessWidth), newValueTmp, address, successBoolResultTmp);
2150 append(BranchTest32, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::Zero), successBoolResultTmp, successBoolResultTmp);
2151 storeBlock->setSuccessors(doneBlock, reloopBlock);
2152
2153 m_currentBlock = strongFailBlock;
2154 {
2155 TypedTmp tmp = newTmp();
2156 appendEffectful(OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(StoreCondRel, accessWidth), valueResultTmp, address, tmp);
2157 append(BranchTest32, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::Zero), tmp, tmp);
2158 }
2159 strongFailBlock->setSuccessors(B3::Air::FrequentedBlock(doneBlock), reloopBlock);
2160
2161 m_currentBlock = doneBlock;
2162 return valueResultTmp;
2163}
2164
2165inline TypedTmp AirIRGenerator::emitAtomicLoadOp(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, ExpressionType pointer, uint32_t uoffset)
2166{
2167 TypedTmp newPtr = fixupPointerPlusOffsetForAtomicOps(op, pointer, uoffset);
2168 Arg addrArg = isX86() ? Arg::addr(newPtr) : Arg::simpleAddr(newPtr);
2169
2170 if (accessWidth(op) != B3::Width8) {
2171 emitCheck([&] {
2172 return Inst(BranchTest64, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), newPtr, isX86() ? Arg::bitImm(sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op) - 1) : Arg::bitImm64(sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op) - 1));
2173 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
2174 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
2175 });
2176 }
2177
2178 std::optional<B3::Air::Opcode> opcode;
2179 if (isX86() || isARM64E())
2180 opcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicXchgAdd, accessWidth(op));
2181 B3::Air::Opcode nonAtomicOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(Add, accessWidth(op));
2182
2183 TypedTmp result = valueType.isI64() ? g64() : g32();
2184
2185 if (opcode) {
2186 if (isValidForm(opcode.value(), Arg::Tmp, addrArg.kind(), Arg::Tmp)) {
2187 append(Move, Arg::imm(0), result);
2188 appendEffectful(opcode.value(), result, addrArg, result);
2189 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, result);
2190 return result;
2191 }
2192
2193 if (isValidForm(opcode.value(), Arg::Tmp, addrArg.kind())) {
2194 append(Move, Arg::imm(0), result);
2195 appendEffectful(opcode.value(), result, addrArg);
2196 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, result);
2197 return result;
2198 }
2199 }
2200
2201 appendGeneralAtomic(op, nonAtomicOpcode, B3::Commutative, Arg::imm(0), addrArg, result);
2202 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, result);
2203 return result;
2204}
2205
2206auto AirIRGenerator::atomicLoad(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType& result, uint32_t offset) -> PartialResult
2207{
2208 ASSERT(pointer.tmp().isGP());
2209
2210 if (UNLIKELY(sumOverflows<uint32_t>(offset, sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op)))) {
2211 // FIXME: Even though this is provably out of bounds, it's not a validation error, so we have to handle it
2212 // as a runtime exception. However, this may change: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=166435
2213 auto* patch = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
2214 patch->setGenerator([this] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
2215 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
2216 });
2217 emitPatchpoint(patch, Tmp());
2218
2219 // We won't reach here, so we just pick a random reg.
2220 switch (valueType.kind) {
2221 case TypeKind::I32:
2222 result = g32();
2223 break;
2224 case TypeKind::I64:
2225 result = g64();
2226 break;
2227 default:
2228 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2229 break;
2230 }
2231 } else
2232 result = emitAtomicLoadOp(op, valueType, emitCheckAndPreparePointer(pointer, offset, sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op)), offset);
2233
2234 return { };
2235}
2236
2237inline void AirIRGenerator::emitAtomicStoreOp(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType value, uint32_t uoffset)
2238{
2239 TypedTmp newPtr = fixupPointerPlusOffsetForAtomicOps(op, pointer, uoffset);
2240 Arg addrArg = isX86() ? Arg::addr(newPtr) : Arg::simpleAddr(newPtr);
2241
2242 if (accessWidth(op) != B3::Width8) {
2243 emitCheck([&] {
2244 return Inst(BranchTest64, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), newPtr, isX86() ? Arg::bitImm(sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op) - 1) : Arg::bitImm64(sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op) - 1));
2245 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
2246 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
2247 });
2248 }
2249
2250 std::optional<B3::Air::Opcode> opcode;
2251 if (isX86() || isARM64E())
2252 opcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicXchg, accessWidth(op));
2253 B3::Air::Opcode nonAtomicOpcode = B3::Air::Nop;
2254
2255 if (opcode) {
2256 if (isValidForm(opcode.value(), Arg::Tmp, addrArg.kind(), Arg::Tmp)) {
2257 TypedTmp result = valueType.isI64() ? g64() : g32();
2258 appendEffectful(opcode.value(), value, addrArg, result);
2259 return;
2260 }
2261
2262 if (isValidForm(opcode.value(), Arg::Tmp, addrArg.kind())) {
2263 TypedTmp result = valueType.isI64() ? g64() : g32();
2264 append(Move, value, result);
2265 appendEffectful(opcode.value(), result, addrArg);
2266 return;
2267 }
2268 }
2269
2270 appendGeneralAtomic(op, nonAtomicOpcode, B3::Commutative, value, addrArg, valueType.isI64() ? g64() : g32());
2271}

2273auto AirIRGenerator::atomicStore(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType value, uint32_t offset) -> PartialResult
2274{
2275 ASSERT(pointer.tmp().isGP());
2276
2277 if (UNLIKELY(sumOverflows<uint32_t>(offset, sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op)))) {

2280 auto* throwException = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);

2290
2291TypedTmp AirIRGenerator::emitAtomicBinaryRMWOp(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType value, uint32_t uoffset)
2292{
2293 TypedTmp newPtr = fixupPointerPlusOffsetForAtomicOps(op, pointer, uoffset);
2294 Arg addrArg = isX86() ? Arg::addr(newPtr) : Arg::simpleAddr(newPtr);
2295
2296 if (accessWidth(op) != B3::Width8) {
2297 emitCheck([&] {
2298 return Inst(BranchTest64, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), newPtr, isX86() ? Arg::bitImm(sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op) - 1) : Arg::bitImm64(sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op) - 1));
2299 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
2300 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
2301 });
2302 }
2303
2304 std::optional<B3::Air::Opcode> opcode;
2305 B3::Air::Opcode nonAtomicOpcode = B3::Air::Nop;
2306 B3::Commutativity commutativity = B3::NotCommutative;
2307 switch (op) {
2308 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw8AddU:
2309 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw16AddU:
2310 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmwAdd:
2311 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw8AddU:
2312 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw16AddU:
2313 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw32AddU:
2314 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmwAdd:
2315 if (isX86() || isARM64E())
2316 opcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicXchgAdd, accessWidth(op));
2317 nonAtomicOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(Add, accessWidth(op));
2318 commutativity = B3::Commutative;
2319 break;
2320 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw8SubU:
2321 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw16SubU:
2322 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmwSub:
2323 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw8SubU:
2324 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw16SubU:
2325 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw32SubU:
2326 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmwSub:
2327 if (isX86() || isARM64E()) {
2328 TypedTmp newValue;
2329 if (valueType.isI64()) {
2330 newValue = g64();
2331 append(Move, value, newValue);
2332 append(Neg64, newValue);
2333 } else {
2334 newValue = g32();
2335 append(Move, value, newValue);
2336 append(Neg32, newValue);
2337 }
2338 value = newValue;
2339 opcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicXchgAdd, accessWidth(op));
2340 nonAtomicOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(Add, accessWidth(op));
2341 commutativity = B3::Commutative;
2342 } else {
2343 nonAtomicOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(Sub, accessWidth(op));
2344 commutativity = B3::NotCommutative;
2345 }
2346 break;
2347 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw8AndU:
2348 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw16AndU:
2349 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmwAnd:
2350 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw8AndU:
2351 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw16AndU:
2352 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw32AndU:
2353 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmwAnd:
2354 if (isARM64E()) {
2355 TypedTmp newValue;
2356 if (valueType.isI64()) {
2357 newValue = g64();
2358 append(Not64, value, newValue);
2359 } else {
2360 newValue = g32();
2361 append(Not32, value, newValue);
2362 }
2363 value = newValue;
2364 opcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicXchgClear, accessWidth(op));
2365 }
2366 nonAtomicOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(And, accessWidth(op));
2367 commutativity = B3::Commutative;
2368 break;
2369 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw8OrU:
2370 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw16OrU:
2371 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmwOr:
2372 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw8OrU:
2373 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw16OrU:
2374 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw32OrU:
2375 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmwOr:
2376 if (isARM64E())
2377 opcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicXchgOr, accessWidth(op));
2378 nonAtomicOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(Or, accessWidth(op));
2379 commutativity = B3::Commutative;
2380 break;
2381 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw8XorU:
2382 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw16XorU:
2383 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmwXor:
2384 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw8XorU:
2385 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw16XorU:
2386 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw32XorU:
2387 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmwXor:
2388 if (isARM64E())
2389 opcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicXchgXor, accessWidth(op));
2390 nonAtomicOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(Xor, accessWidth(op));
2391 commutativity = B3::Commutative;
2392 break;
2393 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw8XchgU:
2394 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmw16XchgU:
2395 case ExtAtomicOpType::I32AtomicRmwXchg:
2396 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw8XchgU:
2397 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw16XchgU:
2398 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmw32XchgU:
2399 case ExtAtomicOpType::I64AtomicRmwXchg:
2400 if (isX86() || isARM64E())
2401 opcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicXchg, accessWidth(op));
2402 nonAtomicOpcode = B3::Air::Nop;
2403 break;
2404 default:
2405 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2406 break;
2407 }
2408
2409 TypedTmp result = valueType.isI64() ? g64() : g32();
2410
2411 if (opcode) {
2412 if (isValidForm(opcode.value(), Arg::Tmp, addrArg.kind(), Arg::Tmp)) {
2413 appendEffectful(opcode.value(), value, addrArg, result);
2414 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, result);
2415 return result;
2416 }
2417
2418 if (isValidForm(opcode.value(), Arg::Tmp, addrArg.kind())) {
2419 append(Move, value, result);
2420 appendEffectful(opcode.value(), result, addrArg);
2421 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, result);
2422 return result;
2423 }
2424 }
2425
2426 appendGeneralAtomic(op, nonAtomicOpcode, commutativity, value, addrArg, result);
2427 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, result);
2428 return result;
2429}
2430
2431auto AirIRGenerator::atomicBinaryRMW(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType value, ExpressionType& result, uint32_t offset) -> PartialResult
2432{
2433 ASSERT(pointer.tmp().isGP());
2434
2435 if (UNLIKELY(sumOverflows<uint32_t>(offset, sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op)))) {
2436 // FIXME: Even though this is provably out of bounds, it's not a validation error, so we have to handle it
2437 // as a runtime exception. However, this may change: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=166435
2438 auto* patch = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
2439 patch->setGenerator([this] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
2440 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
2441 });
2442 emitPatchpoint(patch, Tmp());
2443
2444 switch (valueType.kind) {
2445 case TypeKind::I32:
2446 result = g32();
2447 break;
2448 case TypeKind::I64:
2449 result = g64();
2450 break;
2451 default:
2452 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2453 break;
2454 }
2455 } else
2456 result = emitAtomicBinaryRMWOp(op, valueType, emitCheckAndPreparePointer(pointer, offset, sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op)), value, offset);
2457
2458 return { };
2459}
2460
2461TypedTmp AirIRGenerator::emitAtomicCompareExchange(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType expected, ExpressionType value, uint32_t uoffset)
2462{
2463 TypedTmp newPtr = fixupPointerPlusOffsetForAtomicOps(op, pointer, uoffset);
2464 Arg addrArg = isX86() ? Arg::addr(newPtr) : Arg::simpleAddr(newPtr);
2465 B3::Width valueWidth = widthForType(toB3Type(valueType));
2466 B3::Width accessWidth = Wasm::accessWidth(op);
2467
2468 if (accessWidth != B3::Width8) {
2469 emitCheck([&] {
2470 return Inst(BranchTest64, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), newPtr, isX86() ? Arg::bitImm(sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op) - 1) : Arg::bitImm64(sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op) - 1));
2471 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
2472 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
2473 });
2474 }
2475
2476 TypedTmp result = valueType.isI64() ? g64() : g32();
2477
2478 if (valueWidth == accessWidth) {
2479 appendStrongCAS(op, expected, value, addrArg, result);
2480 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, result);
2481 return result;
2482 }
2483
2484 BasicBlock* failureCase = m_code.addBlock();
2485 BasicBlock* successCase = m_code.addBlock();
2486 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
2487
2488 TypedTmp truncatedExpected = valueType.isI64() ? g64() : g32();
2489 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, expected, truncatedExpected);
2490
2491 append(OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(Branch, valueWidth), Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::NotEqual), expected, truncatedExpected);
2492 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(B3::Air::FrequentedBlock(failureCase, B3::FrequencyClass::Rare), successCase);
2493
2494 m_currentBlock = successCase;
2495 appendStrongCAS(op, expected, value, addrArg, result);
2496 append(Jump);
2497 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(continuation);
2498
2499 m_currentBlock = failureCase;
2500 ([&] {
2501 std::optional<B3::Air::Opcode> opcode;
2502 if (isX86() || isARM64E())
2503 opcode = OPCODE_FOR_WIDTH(AtomicXchgAdd, accessWidth);
2504 B3::Air::Opcode nonAtomicOpcode = OPCODE_FOR_CANONICAL_WIDTH(Add, accessWidth);
2505
2506 if (opcode) {
2507 if (isValidForm(opcode.value(), Arg::Tmp, addrArg.kind(), Arg::Tmp)) {
2508 append(Move, Arg::imm(0), result);
2509 appendEffectful(opcode.value(), result, addrArg, result);
2510 return;
2511 }
2512
2513 if (isValidForm(opcode.value(), Arg::Tmp, addrArg.kind())) {
2514 append(Move, Arg::imm(0), result);
2515 appendEffectful(opcode.value(), result, addrArg);
2516 return;
2517 }
2518 }
2519 appendGeneralAtomic(op, nonAtomicOpcode, B3::Commutative, Arg::imm(0), addrArg, result);
2520 })();
2521 append(Jump);
2522 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(continuation);
2523
2524 m_currentBlock = continuation;
2525 sanitizeAtomicResult(op, valueType, result);
2526 return result;
2527}

2529auto AirIRGenerator::atomicCompareExchange(ExtAtomicOpType op, Type valueType, ExpressionType pointer, ExpressionType expected, ExpressionType value, ExpressionType& result, uint32_t offset) -> PartialResult
2530{
2531 ASSERT(pointer.tmp().isGP());
2532
2533 if (UNLIKELY(sumOverflows<uint32_t>(offset, sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op)))) {
2534 // FIXME: Even though this is provably out of bounds, it's not a validation error, so we have to handle it
2535 // as a runtime exception. However, this may change: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=166435
2536 auto* patch = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
2537 patch->setGenerator([this] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
2538 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsMemoryAccess);
2539 });
2540 emitPatchpoint(patch, Tmp());
2541
2542 // We won't reach here, so we just pick a random reg.
2543 switch (valueType.kind) {
2544 case TypeKind::I32:
2545 result = g32();
2546 break;
2547 case TypeKind::I64:
2548 result = g64();
2549 break;
2550 default:
2551 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2552 }
2553 } else
2554 result = emitAtomicCompareExchange(op, valueType, emitCheckAndPreparePointer(pointer, offset, sizeOfAtomicOpMemoryAccess(op)), expected, value, offset);
2555
2556 return { };
2557}
