2595
2596auto AirIRGenerator::truncSaturated(Ext1OpType op, ExpressionType arg, ExpressionType& result, Type returnType, Type operandType) -> PartialResult
2597{
2598 TypedTmp maxFloat;
2599 TypedTmp minFloat;
2600 TypedTmp signBitConstant;
2601 bool requiresMacroScratchRegisters = false;
2602 switch (op) {
2603 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF32S:
2604 maxFloat = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(-static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min())));
2605 minFloat = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min())));
2606 break;
2607 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF32U:
2608 maxFloat = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) * static_cast<float>(-2.0)));
2609 minFloat = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(static_cast<float>(-1.0)));
2610 break;
2611 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF64S:
2612 maxFloat = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(-static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min())));
2613 minFloat = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) - 1.0));
2614 break;
2615 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF64U:
2616 maxFloat = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) * -2.0));
2617 minFloat = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(-1.0));
2618 break;
2619 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF32S:
2620 maxFloat = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(-static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min())));
2621 minFloat = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min())));
2622 break;
2623 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF32U:
2624 maxFloat = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()) * static_cast<float>(-2.0)));
2625 minFloat = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(static_cast<float>(-1.0)));
2626 if (isX86())
2627 signBitConstant = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max() - std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max())));
2628 requiresMacroScratchRegisters = true;
2629 break;
2630 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF64S:
2631 maxFloat = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(-static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min())));
2632 minFloat = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min())));
2633 break;
2634 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF64U:
2635 maxFloat = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()) * -2.0));
2636 minFloat = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(-1.0));
2637 if (isX86())
2638 signBitConstant = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max() - std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max())));
2639 requiresMacroScratchRegisters = true;
2640 break;
2641 default:
2642 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2643 break;
2644 }
2645
2646 uint64_t minResult = 0;
2647 uint64_t maxResult = 0;
2648 switch (op) {
2649 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF32S:
2650 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF64S:
2651 maxResult = bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(INT32_MAX);
2652 minResult = bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(INT32_MIN);
2653 break;
2654 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF32U:
2655 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF64U:
2656 maxResult = bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(UINT32_MAX);
2657 minResult = bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(0U);
2658 break;
2659 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF32S:
2660 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF64S:
2661 maxResult = bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(INT64_MAX);
2662 minResult = bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(INT64_MIN);
2663 break;
2664 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF32U:
2665 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF64U:
2666 maxResult = bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(UINT64_MAX);
2667 minResult = bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(0ULL);
2668 break;
2669 default:
2670 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2671 break;
2672 }
2673
2674 result = tmpForType(returnType);
2675
2676 BasicBlock* minCase = m_code.addBlock();
2677 BasicBlock* maxCheckCase = m_code.addBlock();
2678 BasicBlock* maxCase = m_code.addBlock();
2679 BasicBlock* inBoundsCase = m_code.addBlock();
2680 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
2681
2682 auto branchOp = operandType == Types::F32 ? BranchFloat : BranchDouble;
2683 append(m_currentBlock, branchOp, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleLessThanOrEqualOrUnordered), arg, minFloat);
2684 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(minCase, maxCheckCase);
2685
2686 append(maxCheckCase, branchOp, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleGreaterThanOrEqualOrUnordered), arg, maxFloat);
2687 maxCheckCase->setSuccessors(maxCase, inBoundsCase);
2688
2689 if (!minResult) {
2690 append(minCase, Move, Arg::bigImm(minResult), result);
2691 append(minCase, Jump);
2692 minCase->setSuccessors(continuation);
2693 } else {
2694 BasicBlock* minMaterializeCase = m_code.addBlock();
2695 BasicBlock* nanCase = m_code.addBlock();
2696 append(minCase, branchOp, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleEqualAndOrdered), arg, arg);
2697 minCase->setSuccessors(minMaterializeCase, nanCase);
2698
2699 append(minMaterializeCase, Move, Arg::bigImm(minResult), result);
2700 append(minMaterializeCase, Jump);
2701 minMaterializeCase->setSuccessors(continuation);
2702
2703 append(nanCase, Move, Arg::bigImm(0), result);
2704 append(nanCase, Jump);
2705 nanCase->setSuccessors(continuation);
2706 }
2707
2708 append(maxCase, Move, Arg::bigImm(maxResult), result);
2709 append(maxCase, Jump);
2710 maxCase->setSuccessors(continuation);
2711
2712 Vector<ConstrainedTmp, 2> args;
2713 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(toB3Type(returnType));
2714 patchpoint->effects = B3::Effects::none();
2715 args.append(arg);
2716 if (requiresMacroScratchRegisters) {
2717 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
2718 if (isX86()) {
2719 args.append(signBitConstant);
2720 patchpoint->numFPScratchRegisters = 1;
2721 }
2722 }
2723
2724 patchpoint->effects = B3::Effects::none();
2725 patchpoint->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
2726 switch (op) {
2727 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF32S:
2728 jit.truncateFloatToInt32(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr());
2729 break;
2730 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF32U:
2731 jit.truncateFloatToUint32(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr());
2732 break;
2733 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF64S:
2734 jit.truncateDoubleToInt32(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr());
2735 break;
2736 case Ext1OpType::I32TruncSatF64U:
2737 jit.truncateDoubleToUint32(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr());
2738 break;
2739 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF32S:
2740 jit.truncateFloatToInt64(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr());
2741 break;
2742 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF32U: {
2743 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
2744 ASSERT(requiresMacroScratchRegisters);
2745 FPRReg scratch = InvalidFPRReg;
2746 FPRReg constant = InvalidFPRReg;
2747 if (isX86()) {
2748 scratch = params.fpScratch(0);
2749 constant = params[2].fpr();
2750 }
2751 jit.truncateFloatToUint64(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr(), scratch, constant);
2752 break;
2753 }
2754 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF64S:
2755 jit.truncateDoubleToInt64(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr());
2756 break;
2757 case Ext1OpType::I64TruncSatF64U: {
2758 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
2759 ASSERT(requiresMacroScratchRegisters);
2760 FPRReg scratch = InvalidFPRReg;
2761 FPRReg constant = InvalidFPRReg;
2762 if (isX86()) {
2763 scratch = params.fpScratch(0);
2764 constant = params[2].fpr();
2765 }
2766 jit.truncateDoubleToUint64(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr(), scratch, constant);
2767 break;
2768 }
2769 default:
2770 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2771 break;
2772 }
2773 });
2774
2775 emitPatchpoint(inBoundsCase, patchpoint, Vector<TypedTmp, 8> { result }, WTFMove(args));
2776 append(inBoundsCase, Jump);
2777 inBoundsCase->setSuccessors(continuation);
2778
2779 m_currentBlock = continuation;
2780
2781 return { };
2782}
2783
2784auto AirIRGenerator::addSelect(ExpressionType condition, ExpressionType nonZero, ExpressionType zero, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
2785{
2786 ASSERT(nonZero.type() == zero.type());
2787 result = tmpForType(nonZero.type());
2788 append(moveOpForValueType(nonZero.type()), nonZero, result);
2789
2790 BasicBlock* isZero = m_code.addBlock();
2791 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
2792
2793 append(BranchTest32, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::Zero), condition, condition);
2794 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(isZero, continuation);
2795
2796 append(isZero, moveOpForValueType(zero.type()), zero, result);
2797 append(isZero, Jump);
2798 isZero->setSuccessors(continuation);
2799
2800 m_currentBlock = continuation;
2801
2802 return { };
2803}
2804
2805void AirIRGenerator::emitEntryTierUpCheck()
2806{
2807 if (!m_tierUp)
2808 return;
2809
2810 auto countdownPtr = g64();
2811 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(bitwise_cast<uintptr_t>(&m_tierUp->m_counter)), countdownPtr);
2812
2813 auto* patch = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
2814 B3::Effects effects = B3::Effects::none();
2815 effects.reads = B3::HeapRange::top();
2816 effects.writes = B3::HeapRange::top();
2817 patch->effects = effects;
2818 patch->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
2819
2820 patch->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
2821 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
2822
2823 CCallHelpers::Jump tierUp = jit.branchAdd32(CCallHelpers::PositiveOrZero, CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(TierUpCount::functionEntryIncrement()), CCallHelpers::Address(params[0].gpr()));
2824 CCallHelpers::Label tierUpResume = jit.label();
2825
2826 params.addLatePath([=] (CCallHelpers& jit) {
2827 tierUp.link(&jit);
2828
2829 const unsigned extraPaddingBytes = 0;
2830 RegisterSet registersToSpill = { };
2831 registersToSpill.add(GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
2832 unsigned numberOfStackBytesUsedForRegisterPreservation = ScratchRegisterAllocator::preserveRegistersToStackForCall(jit, registersToSpill, extraPaddingBytes);
2833
2834 jit.move(MacroAssembler::TrustedImm32(m_functionIndex), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
2835 MacroAssembler::Call call = jit.nearCall();
2836
2837 ScratchRegisterAllocator::restoreRegistersFromStackForCall(jit, registersToSpill, RegisterSet(), numberOfStackBytesUsedForRegisterPreservation, extraPaddingBytes);
2838 jit.jump(tierUpResume);
2839
2840 jit.addLinkTask([=] (LinkBuffer& linkBuffer) {
2841 MacroAssembler::repatchNearCall(linkBuffer.locationOfNearCall<NoPtrTag>(call), CodeLocationLabel<JITThunkPtrTag>(Thunks::singleton().stub(triggerOMGEntryTierUpThunkGenerator).code()));
2842 });
2843 });
2844 });
2845
2846 emitPatchpoint(patch, Tmp(), countdownPtr);
2847}
2848
2849void AirIRGenerator::emitLoopTierUpCheck(uint32_t loopIndex, const Stack& enclosingStack)
2850{
2851 uint32_t outerLoopIndex = this->outerLoopIndex();
2852 m_outerLoops.append(loopIndex);
2853
2854 if (!m_tierUp)
2855 return;
2856
2857 ASSERT(m_tierUp->osrEntryTriggers().size() == loopIndex);
2858 m_tierUp->osrEntryTriggers().append(TierUpCount::TriggerReason::DontTrigger);
2859 m_tierUp->outerLoops().append(outerLoopIndex);
2860
2861 auto countdownPtr = g64();
2862 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(bitwise_cast<uintptr_t>(&m_tierUp->m_counter)), countdownPtr);
2863
2864 auto* patch = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
2865 B3::Effects effects = B3::Effects::none();
2866 effects.reads = B3::HeapRange::top();
2867 effects.writes = B3::HeapRange::top();
2868 effects.exitsSideways = true;
2869 patch->effects = effects;
2870
2871 patch->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
2872 RegisterSet clobberLate;
2873 clobberLate.add(GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2874 patch->clobberLate(clobberLate);
2875
2876 Vector<ConstrainedTmp> patchArgs;
2877 patchArgs.append(countdownPtr);
2878
2879 for (auto& local : m_locals)
2880 patchArgs.append(ConstrainedTmp(local, B3::ValueRep::ColdAny));
2881 for (unsigned controlIndex = 0; controlIndex < m_parser->controlStack().size(); ++controlIndex) {
2882 Stack& expressionStack = m_parser->controlStack()[controlIndex].enclosedExpressionStack;
2883 for (TypedExpression value : expressionStack)
2884 patchArgs.append(ConstrainedTmp(value.value(), B3::ValueRep::ColdAny));
2885 }
2886 for (TypedExpression value : enclosingStack)
2887 patchArgs.append(ConstrainedTmp(value.value(), B3::ValueRep::ColdAny));
2888
2889 TierUpCount::TriggerReason* forceEntryTrigger = &(m_tierUp->osrEntryTriggers().last());
2890 static_assert(!static_cast<uint8_t>(TierUpCount::TriggerReason::DontTrigger), "the JIT code assumes non-zero means 'enter'");
2891 static_assert(sizeof(TierUpCount::TriggerReason) == 1, "branchTest8 assumes this size");
2892 patch->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
2893 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
2894 CCallHelpers::Jump forceOSREntry = jit.branchTest8(CCallHelpers::NonZero, CCallHelpers::AbsoluteAddress(forceEntryTrigger));
2895 CCallHelpers::Jump tierUp = jit.branchAdd32(CCallHelpers::PositiveOrZero, CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(TierUpCount::loopIncrement()), CCallHelpers::Address(params[0].gpr()));
2896 MacroAssembler::Label tierUpResume = jit.label();
2897
2898 OSREntryData& osrEntryData = m_tierUp->addOSREntryData(m_functionIndex, loopIndex);
2899 // First argument is the countdown location.
2900 for (unsigned index = 1; index < params.value()->numChildren(); ++index)
2901 osrEntryData.values().constructAndAppend(params[index], params.value()->child(index)->type());
2902 OSREntryData* osrEntryDataPtr = &osrEntryData;
2903
2904 params.addLatePath([=] (CCallHelpers& jit) {
2905 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
2906 forceOSREntry.link(&jit);
2907 tierUp.link(&jit);
2908
2909 jit.probe(tagCFunction<JITProbePtrTag>(operationWasmTriggerOSREntryNow), osrEntryDataPtr);
2910 jit.branchTestPtr(CCallHelpers::Zero, GPRInfo::argumentGPR0).linkTo(tierUpResume, &jit);
2911 jit.farJump(GPRInfo::argumentGPR1, WasmEntryPtrTag);
2912 });
2913 });
2914
2915 emitPatchpoint(m_currentBlock, patch, ResultList { }, WTFMove(patchArgs));
2916}

2918AirIRGenerator::ControlData AirIRGenerator::addTopLevel(BlockSignature signature)

2923auto AirIRGenerator::addLoop(BlockSignature signature, Stack& enclosingStack, ControlType& block, Stack& newStack, uint32_t loopIndex) -> PartialResult
2924{
2925 BasicBlock* body = m_code.addBlock();
2926 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
2927
2928 splitStack(signature, enclosingStack, newStack);
2929 ResultList results;
2930 results.reserveInitialCapacity(newStack.size());
2931 for (auto item : newStack)
2932 results.uncheckedAppend(item);
2933 block = ControlData(origin(), signature, WTFMove(results), BlockType::Loop, continuation, body);
2934
2935 append(Jump);
2936 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(body);
2937
2938 m_currentBlock = body;
2939 emitLoopTierUpCheck(loopIndex, enclosingStack);
2940
2941 return { };
2942}

2944auto AirIRGenerator::addBlock(BlockSignature signature, Stack& enclosingStack, ControlType& newBlock, Stack& newStack) -> PartialResult
2945{
2946 splitStack(signature, enclosingStack, newStack);
2947 newBlock = ControlData(origin(), signature, tmpsForSignature(signature), BlockType::Block, m_code.addBlock());
2948 return { };

2951auto AirIRGenerator::addIf(ExpressionType condition, BlockSignature signature, Stack& enclosingStack, ControlType& result, Stack& newStack) -> PartialResult
2952{
2953 BasicBlock* taken = m_code.addBlock();
2954 BasicBlock* notTaken = m_code.addBlock();
2955 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
2956
2957 // Wasm bools are i32.
2958 append(BranchTest32, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), condition, condition);
2959 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(taken, notTaken);
2960
2961 m_currentBlock = taken;
2962 splitStack(signature, enclosingStack, newStack);
2963 result = ControlData(origin(), signature, tmpsForSignature(signature), BlockType::If, continuation, notTaken);
2964 return { };
2965}

2983auto AirIRGenerator::addReturn(const ControlData& data, const Stack& returnValues) -> PartialResult
2984{
2985 CallInformation wasmCallInfo = wasmCallingConvention().callInformationFor(*data.signature(), CallRole::Callee);
2986 if (!wasmCallInfo.results.size()) {
2987 append(RetVoid);
2988 return { };
2989 }
2990
2991 B3::PatchpointValue* patch = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
2992 patch->setGenerator([] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
2993 auto calleeSaves = params.code().calleeSaveRegisterAtOffsetList();
2994 jit.emitRestore(calleeSaves);
2995 jit.emitFunctionEpilogue();
2996 jit.ret();
2997 });
2998 patch->effects.terminal = true;
2999
3000 ASSERT(returnValues.size() >= wasmCallInfo.results.size());
3001 unsigned offset = returnValues.size() - wasmCallInfo.results.size();
3002 Vector<ConstrainedTmp, 8> returnConstraints;
3003 for (unsigned i = 0; i < wasmCallInfo.results.size(); ++i) {
3004 B3::ValueRep rep = wasmCallInfo.results[i];
3005 TypedTmp tmp = returnValues[offset + i];
3006
3007 if (rep.isStack()) {
3008 append(moveForType(toB3Type(tmp.type())), tmp, Arg::addr(Tmp(GPRInfo::callFrameRegister), rep.offsetFromFP()));
3009 continue;
3010 }
3011
3012 ASSERT(rep.isReg());
3013 if (data.signature()->returnType(i).isI32())
3014 append(Move32, tmp, tmp);
3015 returnConstraints.append(ConstrainedTmp(tmp, wasmCallInfo.results[i]));
3016 }
3017
3018 emitPatchpoint(m_currentBlock, patch, ResultList { }, WTFMove(returnConstraints));
3019 return { };
3020}

3024auto AirIRGenerator::addBranch(ControlData& data, ExpressionType condition, const Stack& returnValues) -> PartialResult
3025{
3026 unifyValuesWithBlock(returnValues, data.results);
3027
3028 BasicBlock* target = data.targetBlockForBranch();
3029 if (condition) {
3030 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
3031 append(BranchTest32, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), condition, condition);
3032 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(target, continuation);
3033 m_currentBlock = continuation;
3034 } else {
3035 append(Jump);
3036 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(target);
3037 }
3038
3039 return { };

3042auto AirIRGenerator::addSwitch(ExpressionType condition, const Vector<ControlData*>& targets, ControlData& defaultTarget, const Stack& expressionStack) -> PartialResult
3043{
3044 auto& successors = m_currentBlock->successors();
3045 ASSERT(successors.isEmpty());
3046 for (const auto& target : targets) {
3047 unifyValuesWithBlock(expressionStack, target->results);
3048 successors.append(target->targetBlockForBranch());
3049 }
3050 unifyValuesWithBlock(expressionStack, defaultTarget.results);
3051 successors.append(defaultTarget.targetBlockForBranch());
3052
3053 ASSERT(condition.type().isI32());
3054
3055 // FIXME: We should consider dynamically switching between a jump table
3056 // and a binary switch depending on the number of successors.
3057 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=194477
3058
3059 size_t numTargets = targets.size();
3060
3061 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
3062 patchpoint->effects = B3::Effects::none();
3063 patchpoint->effects.terminal = true;
3064 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
3065
3066 patchpoint->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
3067 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
3068
3069 Vector<int64_t> cases;
3070 cases.reserveInitialCapacity(numTargets);
3071 for (size_t i = 0; i < numTargets; ++i)
3072 cases.uncheckedAppend(i);
3073
3074 GPRReg valueReg = params[0].gpr();
3075 BinarySwitch binarySwitch(valueReg, cases, BinarySwitch::Int32);
3076
3077 Vector<CCallHelpers::Jump> caseJumps;
3078 caseJumps.resize(numTargets);
3079
3080 while (binarySwitch.advance(jit)) {
3081 unsigned value = binarySwitch.caseValue();
3082 unsigned index = binarySwitch.caseIndex();
3083 ASSERT_UNUSED(value, value == index);
3084 ASSERT(index < numTargets);
3085 caseJumps[index] = jit.jump();
3086 }
3087
3088 CCallHelpers::JumpList fallThrough = binarySwitch.fallThrough();
3089
3090 Vector<Box<CCallHelpers::Label>> successorLabels = params.successorLabels();
3091 ASSERT(successorLabels.size() == caseJumps.size() + 1);
3092
3093 params.addLatePath([=, caseJumps = WTFMove(caseJumps), successorLabels = WTFMove(successorLabels)] (CCallHelpers& jit) {
3094 for (size_t i = 0; i < numTargets; ++i)
3095 caseJumps[i].linkTo(*successorLabels[i], &jit);
3096 fallThrough.linkTo(*successorLabels[numTargets], &jit);
3097 });
3098 });
3099
3100 emitPatchpoint(patchpoint, TypedTmp(), condition);
3101
3102 return { };
3103}

3105auto AirIRGenerator::endBlock(ControlEntry& entry, Stack& expressionStack) -> PartialResult
3106{
3107 ControlData& data = entry.controlData;
3108
3109 if (data.blockType() != BlockType::Loop)
3110 unifyValuesWithBlock(expressionStack, data.results);
3111 append(Jump);
3112 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(data.continuation);
3113
3114 return addEndToUnreachable(entry, expressionStack);
3115}

3117
3118auto AirIRGenerator::addEndToUnreachable(ControlEntry& entry, const Stack& expressionStack) -> PartialResult
3119{
3120 ControlData& data = entry.controlData;
3121 m_currentBlock = data.continuation;
3122
3123 if (data.blockType() == BlockType::If) {
3124 append(data.special, Jump);
3125 data.special->setSuccessors(m_currentBlock);
3126 }
3127
3128 if (data.blockType() == BlockType::Loop) {
3129 m_outerLoops.removeLast();
3130 for (unsigned i = 0; i < data.signature()->returnCount(); ++i) {
3131 if (i < expressionStack.size())
3132 entry.enclosedExpressionStack.append(expressionStack[i]);
3133 else {
3134 Type type = data.signature()->returnType(i);
3135 entry.enclosedExpressionStack.constructAndAppend(type, addBottom(m_currentBlock, type));
3136 }
3137 }
3138 } else {
3139 for (unsigned i = 0; i < data.signature()->returnCount(); ++i)
3140 entry.enclosedExpressionStack.constructAndAppend(data.signature()->returnType(i), data.results[i]);
3141 }
3142
3143 // TopLevel does not have any code after this so we need to make sure we emit a return here.
3144 if (data.blockType() == BlockType::TopLevel)
3145 return addReturn(data, entry.enclosedExpressionStack);
3146
3147 return { };
3148}

3150B3::PatchpointValue* AirIRGenerator::emitCallPatchpoint(BasicBlock* block, const Signature& signature, const ResultList& results, const Vector<TypedTmp>& args, Vector<ConstrainedTmp>&& patchArgs)
3151{
3152 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(toB3ResultType(&signature));
3153 patchpoint->effects.writesPinned = true;
3154 patchpoint->effects.readsPinned = true;
3155 patchpoint->clobberEarly(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
3156 patchpoint->clobberLate(RegisterSet::volatileRegistersForJSCall());
3157
3158 CallInformation locations = wasmCallingConvention().callInformationFor(signature);
3159 m_code.requestCallArgAreaSizeInBytes(WTF::roundUpToMultipleOf(stackAlignmentBytes(), locations.headerAndArgumentStackSizeInBytes));
3160
3161 size_t offset = patchArgs.size();
3162 Checked<size_t> newSize = checkedSum<size_t>(patchArgs.size(), args.size());
3163 RELEASE_ASSERT(!newSize.hasOverflowed());
3164
3165 patchArgs.grow(newSize);
3166 for (unsigned i = 0; i < args.size(); ++i)
3167 patchArgs[i + offset] = ConstrainedTmp(args[i], locations.params[i]);
3168
3169 if (patchpoint->type() != B3::Void) {
3170 Vector<B3::ValueRep, 1> resultConstraints;
3171 for (auto valueLocation : locations.results)
3172 resultConstraints.append(B3::ValueRep(valueLocation));
3173 patchpoint->resultConstraints = WTFMove(resultConstraints);
3174 }
3175 emitPatchpoint(block, patchpoint, results, WTFMove(patchArgs));
3176 return patchpoint;
3177}

3179auto AirIRGenerator::addCall(uint32_t functionIndex, const Signature& signature, Vector<ExpressionType>& args, ResultList& results) -> PartialResult
3180{
3181 ASSERT(signature.argumentCount() == args.size());
3182
3183 m_makesCalls = true;
3184
3185 for (unsigned i = 0; i < signature.returnCount(); ++i)
3186 results.append(tmpForType(signature.returnType(i)));
3187
3188 Vector<UnlinkedWasmToWasmCall>* unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls = &m_unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls;
3189
3190 if (m_info.isImportedFunctionFromFunctionIndexSpace(functionIndex)) {
3191 m_maxNumJSCallArguments = std::max(m_maxNumJSCallArguments, static_cast<uint32_t>(args.size()));
3192
3193 auto currentInstance = g64();
3194 append(Move, instanceValue(), currentInstance);
3195
3196 auto targetInstance = g64();
3197
3198 // FIXME: We should have better isel here.
3199 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=193999
3200 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(Instance::offsetOfTargetInstance(functionIndex)), targetInstance);
3201 append(Add64, instanceValue(), targetInstance);
3202 append(Move, Arg::addr(targetInstance), targetInstance);
3203
3204 BasicBlock* isWasmBlock = m_code.addBlock();
3205 BasicBlock* isEmbedderBlock = m_code.addBlock();
3206 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
3207
3208 append(BranchTest64, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), targetInstance, targetInstance);
3209 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(isWasmBlock, isEmbedderBlock);
3210
3211 {
3212 auto* patchpoint = emitCallPatchpoint(isWasmBlock, signature, results, args);
3213 // We need to clobber all potential pinned registers since we might be leaving the instance.
3214 // We pessimistically assume we could be calling to something that is bounds checking.
3215 // FIXME: We shouldn't have to do this: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=172181
3216 patchpoint->clobberLate(PinnedRegisterInfo::get().toSave(MemoryMode::BoundsChecking));
3217
3218 patchpoint->setGenerator([unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls, functionIndex] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
3219 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
3220 CCallHelpers::Call call = jit.threadSafePatchableNearCall();
3221 jit.addLinkTask([unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls, call, functionIndex] (LinkBuffer& linkBuffer) {
3222 unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls->append({ linkBuffer.locationOfNearCall<WasmEntryPtrTag>(call), functionIndex });
3223 });
3224 });
3225
3226 append(isWasmBlock, Jump);
3227 isWasmBlock->setSuccessors(continuation);
3228 }
3229
3230 {
3231 auto jumpDestination = g64();
3232 append(isEmbedderBlock, Move, Arg::bigImm(Instance::offsetOfWasmToEmbedderStub(functionIndex)), jumpDestination);
3233 append(isEmbedderBlock, Add64, instanceValue(), jumpDestination);
3234 append(isEmbedderBlock, Move, Arg::addr(jumpDestination), jumpDestination);
3235
3236 Vector<ConstrainedTmp> jumpArgs;
3237 jumpArgs.append({ jumpDestination, B3::ValueRep::SomeRegister });
3238 auto* patchpoint = emitCallPatchpoint(isEmbedderBlock, signature, results, args, WTFMove(jumpArgs));
3239 // We need to clobber all potential pinned registers since we might be leaving the instance.
3240 // We pessimistically assume we could be calling to something that is bounds checking.
3241 // FIXME: We shouldn't have to do this: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=172181
3242 patchpoint->clobberLate(PinnedRegisterInfo::get().toSave(MemoryMode::BoundsChecking));
3243 patchpoint->setGenerator([] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
3244 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
3245 jit.call(params[params.proc().resultCount(params.value()->type())].gpr(), WasmEntryPtrTag);
3246 });
3247
3248 append(isEmbedderBlock, Jump);
3249 isEmbedderBlock->setSuccessors(continuation);
3250 }
3251
3252 m_currentBlock = continuation;
3253 // The call could have been to another WebAssembly instance, and / or could have modified our Memory.
3254 restoreWebAssemblyGlobalState(RestoreCachedStackLimit::Yes, m_info.memory, currentInstance, continuation);
3255 } else {
3256 auto* patchpoint = emitCallPatchpoint(m_currentBlock, signature, results, args);
3257 // We need to clobber the size register since the LLInt always bounds checks
3258 if (m_mode == MemoryMode::Signaling || m_info.memory.isShared())
3259 patchpoint->clobberLate(RegisterSet { PinnedRegisterInfo::get().boundsCheckingSizeRegister });
3260 patchpoint->setGenerator([unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls, functionIndex] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
3261 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
3262 CCallHelpers::Call call = jit.threadSafePatchableNearCall();
3263 jit.addLinkTask([unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls, call, functionIndex] (LinkBuffer& linkBuffer) {
3264 unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls->append({ linkBuffer.locationOfNearCall<WasmEntryPtrTag>(call), functionIndex });
3265 });
3266 });
3267 }
3268
3269 return { };
3270}

3272auto AirIRGenerator::addCallIndirect(unsigned tableIndex, const Signature& signature, Vector<ExpressionType>& args, ResultList& results) -> PartialResult
3273{
3274 ExpressionType calleeIndex = args.takeLast();
3275 ASSERT(signature.argumentCount() == args.size());
3276 ASSERT(m_info.tableCount() > tableIndex);
3277 ASSERT(m_info.tables[tableIndex].type() == TableElementType::Funcref);
3278
3279 m_makesCalls = true;
3280 // Note: call indirect can call either WebAssemblyFunction or WebAssemblyWrapperFunction. Because
3281 // WebAssemblyWrapperFunction is like calling into the embedder, we conservatively assume all call indirects
3282 // can be to the embedder for our stack check calculation.
3283 m_maxNumJSCallArguments = std::max(m_maxNumJSCallArguments, static_cast<uint32_t>(args.size()));
3284
3285 ExpressionType callableFunctionBuffer = g64();
3286 ExpressionType instancesBuffer = g64();
3287 ExpressionType callableFunctionBufferLength = g64();
3288 {
3289 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(FuncRefTable::offsetOfFunctions(), B3::Width64));
3290 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(FuncRefTable::offsetOfInstances(), B3::Width64));
3291 RELEASE_ASSERT(Arg::isValidAddrForm(FuncRefTable::offsetOfLength(), B3::Width64));
3292
3293 if (UNLIKELY(!Arg::isValidAddrForm(Instance::offsetOfTablePtr(m_numImportFunctions, tableIndex), B3::Width64))) {
3294 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(Instance::offsetOfTablePtr(m_numImportFunctions, tableIndex)), callableFunctionBufferLength);
3295 append(Add64, instanceValue(), callableFunctionBufferLength);
3296 append(Move, Arg::addr(callableFunctionBufferLength), callableFunctionBufferLength);
3297 } else
3298 append(Move, Arg::addr(instanceValue(), Instance::offsetOfTablePtr(m_numImportFunctions, tableIndex)), callableFunctionBufferLength);
3299 append(Move, Arg::addr(callableFunctionBufferLength, FuncRefTable::offsetOfFunctions()), callableFunctionBuffer);
3300 append(Move, Arg::addr(callableFunctionBufferLength, FuncRefTable::offsetOfInstances()), instancesBuffer);
3301 append(Move32, Arg::addr(callableFunctionBufferLength, Table::offsetOfLength()), callableFunctionBufferLength);
3302 }
3303
3304 append(Move32, calleeIndex, calleeIndex);
3305
3306 // Check the index we are looking for is valid.
3307 emitCheck([&] {
3308 return Inst(Branch32, nullptr, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::AboveOrEqual), calleeIndex, callableFunctionBufferLength);
3309 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
3310 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsCallIndirect);
3311 });
3312
3313 ExpressionType calleeCode = g64();
3314 {
3315 ExpressionType calleeSignatureIndex = g64();
3316 // Compute the offset in the table index space we are looking for.
3317 append(Move, Arg::imm(sizeof(WasmToWasmImportableFunction)), calleeSignatureIndex);
3318 append(Mul64, calleeIndex, calleeSignatureIndex);
3319 append(Add64, callableFunctionBuffer, calleeSignatureIndex);
3320
3321 append(Move, Arg::addr(calleeSignatureIndex, WasmToWasmImportableFunction::offsetOfEntrypointLoadLocation()), calleeCode); // Pointer to callee code.
3322
3323 // Check that the WasmToWasmImportableFunction is initialized. We trap if it isn't. An "invalid" SignatureIndex indicates it's not initialized.
3324 // FIXME: when we have trap handlers, we can just let the call fail because Signature::invalidIndex is 0. https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=177210
3325 static_assert(sizeof(WasmToWasmImportableFunction::signatureIndex) == sizeof(uint64_t), "Load codegen assumes i64");
3326
3327 // FIXME: This seems wasteful to do two checks just for a nicer error message.
3328 // We should move just to use a single branch and then figure out what
3329 // error to use in the exception handler.
3330
3331 append(Move, Arg::addr(calleeSignatureIndex, WasmToWasmImportableFunction::offsetOfSignatureIndex()), calleeSignatureIndex);
3332
3333 emitCheck([&] {
3334 static_assert(Signature::invalidIndex == 0, "");
3335 return Inst(BranchTest64, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::Zero), calleeSignatureIndex, calleeSignatureIndex);
3336 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
3337 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::NullTableEntry);
3338 });
3339
3340 ExpressionType expectedSignatureIndex = g64();
3341 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(SignatureInformation::get(signature)), expectedSignatureIndex);
3342 emitCheck([&] {
3343 return Inst(Branch64, nullptr, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::NotEqual), calleeSignatureIndex, expectedSignatureIndex);
3344 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
3345 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::BadSignature);
3346 });
3347 }
3348
3349 auto calleeInstance = g64();
3350 append(Move, Arg::index(instancesBuffer, calleeIndex, 8, 0), calleeInstance);
3351
3352 return emitIndirectCall(calleeInstance, calleeCode, signature, args, results);
3353}

3355auto AirIRGenerator::addCallRef(const Signature& signature, Vector<ExpressionType>& args, ResultList& results) -> PartialResult
3356{
3357 m_makesCalls = true;
3358 // Note: call ref can call either WebAssemblyFunction or WebAssemblyWrapperFunction. Because
3359 // WebAssemblyWrapperFunction is like calling into the embedder, we conservatively assume all call indirects

3374auto AirIRGenerator::emitIndirectCall(TypedTmp calleeInstance, ExpressionType calleeCode, const Signature& signature, const Vector<ExpressionType>& args, ResultList& results) -> PartialResult
3375{
3376 auto currentInstance = g64();
3377 append(Move, instanceValue(), currentInstance);
3378
3379 // Do a context switch if needed.
3380 {
3381 BasicBlock* doContextSwitch = m_code.addBlock();
3382 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
3383
3384 append(Branch64, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::Equal), calleeInstance, currentInstance);
3385 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(continuation, doContextSwitch);
3386
3387 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(B3::Void);
3388 patchpoint->effects.writesPinned = true;
3389 // We pessimistically assume we're calling something with BoundsChecking memory.
3390 // FIXME: We shouldn't have to do this: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=172181
3391 patchpoint->clobber(PinnedRegisterInfo::get().toSave(MemoryMode::BoundsChecking));
3392 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
3393 patchpoint->numGPScratchRegisters = 1;
3394
3395 patchpoint->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
3396 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
3397 GPRReg calleeInstance = params[0].gpr();
3398 GPRReg oldContextInstance = params[1].gpr();
3399 const PinnedRegisterInfo& pinnedRegs = PinnedRegisterInfo::get();
3400 GPRReg baseMemory = pinnedRegs.baseMemoryPointer;
3401 ASSERT(calleeInstance != baseMemory);
3402 jit.loadPtr(CCallHelpers::Address(oldContextInstance, Instance::offsetOfCachedStackLimit()), baseMemory);
3403 jit.storePtr(baseMemory, CCallHelpers::Address(calleeInstance, Instance::offsetOfCachedStackLimit()));
3404 jit.storeWasmContextInstance(calleeInstance);
3405 // FIXME: We should support more than one memory size register
3406 // see: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=162952
3407 ASSERT(pinnedRegs.boundsCheckingSizeRegister != calleeInstance);
3408 GPRReg scratch = params.gpScratch(0);
3409
3410 jit.loadPtr(CCallHelpers::Address(calleeInstance, Instance::offsetOfCachedBoundsCheckingSize()), pinnedRegs.boundsCheckingSizeRegister); // Bound checking size.
3411 jit.loadPtr(CCallHelpers::Address(calleeInstance, Instance::offsetOfCachedMemory()), baseMemory); // Memory::void*.
3412
3413 jit.cageConditionallyAndUntag(Gigacage::Primitive, baseMemory, pinnedRegs.boundsCheckingSizeRegister, scratch);
3414 });
3415
3416 emitPatchpoint(doContextSwitch, patchpoint, Tmp(), calleeInstance, currentInstance);
3417 append(doContextSwitch, Jump);
3418 doContextSwitch->setSuccessors(continuation);
3419
3420 m_currentBlock = continuation;
3421 }
3422
3423 append(Move, Arg::addr(calleeCode), calleeCode);
3424
3425 Vector<ConstrainedTmp> extraArgs;
3426 extraArgs.append(calleeCode);
3427
3428 for (unsigned i = 0; i < signature.returnCount(); ++i)
3429 results.append(tmpForType(signature.returnType(i)));
3430
3431 auto* patchpoint = emitCallPatchpoint(m_currentBlock, signature, results, args, WTFMove(extraArgs));
3432
3433 // We need to clobber all potential pinned registers since we might be leaving the instance.
3434 // We pessimistically assume we're always calling something that is bounds checking so
3435 // because the wasm->wasm thunk unconditionally overrides the size registers.
3436 // FIXME: We should not have to do this, but the wasm->wasm stub assumes it can
3437 // use all the pinned registers as scratch: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=172181
3438
3439 patchpoint->clobberLate(PinnedRegisterInfo::get().toSave(MemoryMode::BoundsChecking));
3440
3441 patchpoint->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
3442 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
3443 jit.call(params[params.proc().resultCount(params.value()->type())].gpr(), WasmEntryPtrTag);
3444 });
3445
3446 // The call could have been to another WebAssembly instance, and / or could have modified our Memory.
3447 restoreWebAssemblyGlobalState(RestoreCachedStackLimit::Yes, m_info.memory, currentInstance, m_currentBlock);
3448
3449 return { };
3450}
3451
3452void AirIRGenerator::unify(const ExpressionType dst, const ExpressionType source)
3453{
3454 ASSERT(isSubtype(source.type(), dst.type()));
3455 append(moveOpForValueType(dst.type()), source, dst);
3456}
3457
3458void AirIRGenerator::unifyValuesWithBlock(const Stack& resultStack, const ResultList& result)
3459{
3460 ASSERT(result.size() <= resultStack.size());
3461
3462 for (size_t i = 0; i < result.size(); ++i)
3463 unify(result[result.size() - 1 - i], resultStack[resultStack.size() - 1 - i]);
3464}

3466static void dumpExpressionStack(const CommaPrinter& comma, const AirIRGenerator::Stack& expressionStack)
3467{
3468 dataLog(comma, "ExpressionStack:");
3469 for (const auto& expression : expressionStack)
3470 dataLog(comma, expression.value());
3471}
3472
3473void AirIRGenerator::dump(const ControlStack& controlStack, const Stack* stack)
3474{
3475 dataLogLn("Processing Graph:");
3476 dataLog(m_code);
3477 dataLogLn("With current block:", *m_currentBlock);
3478 dataLogLn("Control stack:");
3479 for (size_t i = controlStack.size(); i--;) {
3480 dataLog(" ", controlStack[i].controlData, ": ");
3481 CommaPrinter comma(", ", "");
3482 dumpExpressionStack(comma, *stack);
3483 stack = &controlStack[i].enclosedExpressionStack;
3484 dataLogLn();
3485 }
3486 dataLogLn("\n");
3487}

3489auto AirIRGenerator::origin() -> B3::Origin
3490{
3491 // FIXME: We should implement a way to give Inst's an origin.
3492 return B3::Origin();
3493}
3494
3495Expected<std::unique_ptr<InternalFunction>, String> parseAndCompileAir(CompilationContext& compilationContext, const FunctionData& function, const Signature& signature, Vector<UnlinkedWasmToWasmCall>& unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls, const ModuleInformation& info, MemoryMode mode, uint32_t functionIndex, TierUpCount* tierUp)
3496{
3497 auto result = makeUnique<InternalFunction>();
3498
3499 compilationContext.embedderEntrypointJIT = makeUnique<CCallHelpers>();
3500 compilationContext.wasmEntrypointJIT = makeUnique<CCallHelpers>();
3501
3502 B3::Procedure procedure;
3503 Code& code = procedure.code();
3504
3505 procedure.setOriginPrinter([] (PrintStream& out, B3::Origin origin) {
3506 if (origin.data())
3507 out.print("Wasm: ", bitwise_cast<OpcodeOrigin>(origin));
3508 });
3509
3510 // This means we cannot use either StackmapGenerationParams::usedRegisters() or
3511 // StackmapGenerationParams::unavailableRegisters(). In exchange for this concession, we
3512 // don't strictly need to run Air::reportUsedRegisters(), which saves a bit of CPU time at
3513 // optLevel=1.
3514 procedure.setNeedsUsedRegisters(false);
3515
3516 procedure.setOptLevel(Options::webAssemblyBBQAirOptimizationLevel());
3517
3518 AirIRGenerator irGenerator(info, procedure, result.get(), unlinkedWasmToWasmCalls, mode, functionIndex, tierUp, signature);
3519 FunctionParser<AirIRGenerator> parser(irGenerator, function.data.data(), function.data.size(), signature, info);
3520 WASM_FAIL_IF_HELPER_FAILS(parser.parse());
3521
3522
3523 for (BasicBlock* block : code) {
3524 for (size_t i = 0; i < block->numSuccessors(); ++i)
3525 block->successorBlock(i)->addPredecessor(block);
3526 }
3527
3528 {
3529 if (UNLIKELY(shouldDumpIRAtEachPhase(B3::AirMode))) {
3530 dataLogLn("Generated patchpoints");
3531 for (B3::PatchpointValue** patch : irGenerator.patchpoints())
3532 dataLogLn(deepDump(procedure, *patch));
3533 }
3534
3535 B3::Air::prepareForGeneration(code);
3536 B3::Air::generate(code, *compilationContext.wasmEntrypointJIT);
3537 compilationContext.wasmEntrypointByproducts = procedure.releaseByproducts();
3538 result->entrypoint.calleeSaveRegisters = code.calleeSaveRegisterAtOffsetList();
3539 }
3540
3541 return result;
3542}
3543
3544template <typename IntType>
3545void AirIRGenerator::emitChecksForModOrDiv(bool isSignedDiv, ExpressionType left, ExpressionType right)
3546{
3547 static_assert(sizeof(IntType) == 4 || sizeof(IntType) == 8, "");
3548
3549 emitCheck([&] {
3550 return Inst(sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? BranchTest32 : BranchTest64, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::Zero), right, right);
3551 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
3552 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::DivisionByZero);
3553 });
3554
3555 if (isSignedDiv) {
3556 ASSERT(std::is_signed<IntType>::value);
3557 IntType min = std::numeric_limits<IntType>::min();
3558
3559 // FIXME: Better isel for compare with imms here.
3560 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=193999
3561 auto minTmp = sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? g32() : g64();
3562 auto negOne = sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? g32() : g64();
3563
3564 B3::Air::Opcode op = sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Compare32 : Compare64;
3565 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(static_cast<uint64_t>(min)), minTmp);
3566 append(op, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::Equal), left, minTmp, minTmp);
3567
3568 append(Move, Arg::isValidImmForm(-1) ? Arg::imm(-1) : Arg::bigImm(-1) , negOne);
3569 append(op, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::Equal), right, negOne, negOne);
3570
3571 emitCheck([&] {
3572 return Inst(BranchTest32, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), minTmp, negOne);
3573 },
3574 [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
3575 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::IntegerOverflow);
3576 });
3577 }
3578}
3579
3580template <typename IntType>
3581void AirIRGenerator::emitModOrDiv(bool isDiv, ExpressionType lhs, ExpressionType rhs, ExpressionType& result)
3582{
3583 static_assert(sizeof(IntType) == 4 || sizeof(IntType) == 8, "");
3584
3585 result = sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? g32() : g64();
3586
3587 bool isSigned = std::is_signed<IntType>::value;
3588
3589 if (isARM64()) {
3590 B3::Air::Opcode div;
3591 switch (sizeof(IntType)) {
3592 case 4:
3593 div = isSigned ? Div32 : UDiv32;
3594 break;
3595 case 8:
3596 div = isSigned ? Div64 : UDiv64;
3597 break;
3598 }
3599
3600 append(div, lhs, rhs, result);
3601
3602 if (!isDiv) {
3603 append(sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Mul32 : Mul64, result, rhs, result);
3604 append(sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Sub32 : Sub64, lhs, result, result);
3605 }
3606
3607 return;
3608 }
3609
3610#if CPU(X86_64)
3611 Tmp eax(X86Registers::eax);
3612 Tmp edx(X86Registers::edx);
3613
3614 if (isSigned) {
3615 B3::Air::Opcode convertToDoubleWord;
3616 B3::Air::Opcode div;
3617 switch (sizeof(IntType)) {
3618 case 4:
3619 convertToDoubleWord = X86ConvertToDoubleWord32;
3620 div = X86Div32;
3621 break;
3622 case 8:
3623 convertToDoubleWord = X86ConvertToQuadWord64;
3624 div = X86Div64;
3625 break;
3626 default:
3627 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3628 }
3629
3630 // We implement "res = Div<Chill>/Mod<Chill>(num, den)" as follows:
3631 //
3632 // if (den + 1 <=_unsigned 1) {
3633 // if (!den) {
3634 // res = 0;
3635 // goto done;
3636 // }
3637 // if (num == -2147483648) {
3638 // res = isDiv ? num : 0;
3639 // goto done;
3640 // }
3641 // }
3642 // res = num (/ or %) dev;
3643 // done:
3644
3645 BasicBlock* denIsGood = m_code.addBlock();
3646 BasicBlock* denMayBeBad = m_code.addBlock();
3647 BasicBlock* denNotZero = m_code.addBlock();
3648 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
3649
3650 auto temp = sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? g32() : g64();
3651 auto one = addConstant(sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Types::I32 : Types::I64, 1);
3652
3653 append(sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Add32 : Add64, rhs, one, temp);
3654 append(sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Branch32 : Branch64, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::Above), temp, one);
3655 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(denIsGood, denMayBeBad);
3656
3657 append(denMayBeBad, Xor64, result, result);
3658 append(denMayBeBad, sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? BranchTest32 : BranchTest64, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::Zero), rhs, rhs);
3659 denMayBeBad->setSuccessors(continuation, denNotZero);
3660
3661 auto min = addConstant(denNotZero, sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Types::I32 : Types::I64, std::numeric_limits<IntType>::min());
3662 if (isDiv)
3663 append(denNotZero, sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Move32 : Move, min, result);
3664 else {
3665 // Result is zero, as set above...
3666 }
3667 append(denNotZero, sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Branch32 : Branch64, Arg::relCond(MacroAssembler::Equal), lhs, min);
3668 denNotZero->setSuccessors(continuation, denIsGood);
3669
3670 auto divResult = isDiv ? eax : edx;
3671 append(denIsGood, Move, lhs, eax);
3672 append(denIsGood, convertToDoubleWord, eax, edx);
3673 append(denIsGood, div, eax, edx, rhs);
3674 append(denIsGood, sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Move32 : Move, divResult, result);
3675 append(denIsGood, Jump);
3676 denIsGood->setSuccessors(continuation);
3677
3678 m_currentBlock = continuation;
3679 return;
3680 }
3681
3682 B3::Air::Opcode div = sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? X86UDiv32 : X86UDiv64;
3683
3684 Tmp divResult = isDiv ? eax : edx;
3685
3686 append(Move, lhs, eax);
3687 append(Xor64, edx, edx);
3688 append(div, eax, edx, rhs);
3689 append(sizeof(IntType) == 4 ? Move32 : Move, divResult, result);
3690#else
3691 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3692#endif
3693}
3694

3921template<>
3922auto AirIRGenerator::addOp<OpType::I32TruncSF64>(ExpressionType arg, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
3923{
3924 auto max = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(-static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min())));
3925 auto min = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) - 1.0));
3926
3927 auto temp1 = g32();
3928 auto temp2 = g32();
3929 append(CompareDouble, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleLessThanOrEqualOrUnordered), arg, min, temp1);
3930 append(CompareDouble, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleGreaterThanOrEqualOrUnordered), arg, max, temp2);
3931 append(Or32, temp1, temp2);
3932
3933 emitCheck([&] {
3934 return Inst(BranchTest32, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), temp2, temp2);
3935 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
3936 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsTrunc);
3937 });
3938
3939 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(B3::Int32);
3940 patchpoint->effects = B3::Effects::none();
3941 patchpoint->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
3942 jit.truncateDoubleToInt32(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr());
3943 });
3944 result = g32();
3945 emitPatchpoint(patchpoint, result, arg);
3946
3947 return { };
3948}
3949
3950template<>
3951auto AirIRGenerator::addOp<OpType::I32TruncSF32>(ExpressionType arg, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
3952{
3953 auto max = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(-static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min())));
3954 auto min = addConstant(Types::F32, bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min())));
3955
3956 auto temp1 = g32();
3957 auto temp2 = g32();
3958 append(CompareFloat, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleLessThanOrUnordered), arg, min, temp1);
3959 append(CompareFloat, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleGreaterThanOrEqualOrUnordered), arg, max, temp2);
3960 append(Or32, temp1, temp2);
3961
3962 emitCheck([&] {
3963 return Inst(BranchTest32, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), temp2, temp2);
3964 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
3965 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsTrunc);
3966 });
3967
3968 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(B3::Int32);
3969 patchpoint->effects = B3::Effects::none();
3970 patchpoint->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {

4064template<>
4065auto AirIRGenerator::addOp<OpType::I64TruncUF64>(ExpressionType arg, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
4066{
4067 auto max = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()) * -2.0));
4068 auto min = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(-1.0));
4069
4070 auto temp1 = g32();
4071 auto temp2 = g32();
4072 append(CompareDouble, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleLessThanOrEqualOrUnordered), arg, min, temp1);
4073 append(CompareDouble, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleGreaterThanOrEqualOrUnordered), arg, max, temp2);
4074 append(Or32, temp1, temp2);
4075
4076 emitCheck([&] {
4077 return Inst(BranchTest32, nullptr, Arg::resCond(MacroAssembler::NonZero), temp2, temp2);
4078 }, [=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams&) {
4079 this->emitThrowException(jit, ExceptionType::OutOfBoundsTrunc);
4080 });
4081
4082 TypedTmp signBitConstant;
4083 if (isX86())
4084 signBitConstant = addConstant(Types::F64, bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max() - std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max())));
4085
4086 Vector<ConstrainedTmp> args;
4087 auto* patchpoint = addPatchpoint(B3::Int64);
4088 patchpoint->effects = B3::Effects::none();
4089 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
4090 args.append(arg);
4091 if (isX86()) {
4092 args.append(signBitConstant);
4093 patchpoint->numFPScratchRegisters = 1;
4094 }
4095 patchpoint->setGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, const B3::StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
4096 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
4097 FPRReg scratch = InvalidFPRReg;
4098 FPRReg constant = InvalidFPRReg;
4099 if (isX86()) {
4100 scratch = params.fpScratch(0);
4101 constant = params[2].fpr();
4102 }
4103 jit.truncateDoubleToUint64(params[1].fpr(), params[0].gpr(), scratch, constant);
4104 });
4105
4106 result = g64();
4107 emitPatchpoint(m_currentBlock, patchpoint, Vector<TypedTmp, 8> { result }, WTFMove(args));
4108 return { };
4109}

4186
4187auto AirIRGenerator::addShift(Type type, B3::Air::Opcode op, ExpressionType value, ExpressionType shift, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
4188{
4189 ASSERT(type.isI64() || type.isI32());
4190 result = tmpForType(type);
4191
4192 if (isValidForm(op, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp)) {
4193 append(op, value, shift, result);
4194 return { };
4195 }
4196
4197#if CPU(X86_64)
4198 Tmp ecx = Tmp(X86Registers::ecx);
4199 append(Move, value, result);
4200 append(Move, shift, ecx);
4201 append(op, ecx, result);
4202#else
4203 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4204#endif
4205 return { };
4206}
4207
4208auto AirIRGenerator::addIntegerSub(B3::Air::Opcode op, ExpressionType lhs, ExpressionType rhs, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
4209{
4210 ASSERT(op == Sub32 || op == Sub64);
4211
4212 result = op == Sub32 ? g32() : g64();
4213
4214 if (isValidForm(op, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp)) {
4215 append(op, lhs, rhs, result);
4216 return { };
4217 }
4218
4219 RELEASE_ASSERT(isX86());
4220 // Sub a, b
4221 // means
4222 // b = b Sub a
4223 append(Move, lhs, result);
4224 append(op, rhs, result);
4225 return { };
4226}
4227
4228auto AirIRGenerator::addFloatingPointAbs(B3::Air::Opcode op, ExpressionType value, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
4229{
4230 RELEASE_ASSERT(op == AbsFloat || op == AbsDouble);
4231
4232 result = op == AbsFloat ? f32() : f64();
4233
4234 if (isValidForm(op, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp)) {
4235 append(op, value, result);
4236 return { };
4237 }
4238
4239 RELEASE_ASSERT(isX86());
4240
4241 if (op == AbsFloat) {
4242 auto constant = g32();
4243 append(Move, Arg::imm(static_cast<uint32_t>(~(1ull << 31))), constant);
4244 append(Move32ToFloat, constant, result);
4245 append(AndFloat, value, result);
4246 } else {
4247 auto constant = g64();
4248 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(~(1ull << 63)), constant);
4249 append(Move64ToDouble, constant, result);
4250 append(AndDouble, value, result);
4251 }
4252 return { };
4253}

4255auto AirIRGenerator::addFloatingPointBinOp(Type type, B3::Air::Opcode op, ExpressionType lhs, ExpressionType rhs, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
4256{
4257 ASSERT(type.isF32() || type.isF64());
4258 result = tmpForType(type);
4259
4260 if (isValidForm(op, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp, Arg::Tmp)) {
4261 append(op, lhs, rhs, result);
4262 return { };
4263 }
4264
4265 RELEASE_ASSERT(isX86());
4266
4267 // Op a, b
4268 // means
4269 // b = b Op a
4270 append(moveOpForValueType(type), lhs, result);
4271 append(op, rhs, result);
4272 return { };
4273}

4326
4327auto AirIRGenerator::addFloatingPointMinOrMax(Type floatType, MinOrMax minOrMax, ExpressionType arg0, ExpressionType arg1, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
4328{
4329 ASSERT(floatType.isF32() || floatType.isF64());
4330 result = tmpForType(floatType);
4331
4332 BasicBlock* isEqual = m_code.addBlock();
4333 BasicBlock* notEqual = m_code.addBlock();
4334 BasicBlock* isLessThan = m_code.addBlock();
4335 BasicBlock* notLessThan = m_code.addBlock();
4336 BasicBlock* isGreaterThan = m_code.addBlock();
4337 BasicBlock* isNaN = m_code.addBlock();
4338 BasicBlock* continuation = m_code.addBlock();
4339
4340 auto branchOp = floatType.isF32() ? BranchFloat : BranchDouble;
4341 append(m_currentBlock, branchOp, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleEqualAndOrdered), arg0, arg1);
4342 m_currentBlock->setSuccessors(isEqual, notEqual);
4343
4344 append(notEqual, branchOp, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleLessThanAndOrdered), arg0, arg1);
4345 notEqual->setSuccessors(isLessThan, notLessThan);
4346
4347 append(notLessThan, branchOp, Arg::doubleCond(MacroAssembler::DoubleGreaterThanAndOrdered), arg0, arg1);
4348 notLessThan->setSuccessors(isGreaterThan, isNaN);
4349
4350 auto andOp = floatType.isF32() ? AndFloat : AndDouble;
4351 auto orOp = floatType.isF32() ? OrFloat : OrDouble;
4352 append(isEqual, minOrMax == MinOrMax::Max ? andOp : orOp, arg0, arg1, result);
4353 append(isEqual, Jump);
4354 isEqual->setSuccessors(continuation);
4355
4356 auto isLessThanResult = minOrMax == MinOrMax::Max ? arg1 : arg0;
4357 append(isLessThan, moveOpForValueType(floatType), isLessThanResult, result);
4358 append(isLessThan, Jump);
4359 isLessThan->setSuccessors(continuation);
4360
4361 auto isGreaterThanResult = minOrMax == MinOrMax::Max ? arg0 : arg1;
4362 append(isGreaterThan, moveOpForValueType(floatType), isGreaterThanResult, result);
4363 append(isGreaterThan, Jump);
4364 isGreaterThan->setSuccessors(continuation);
4365
4366 auto addOp = floatType.isF32() ? AddFloat : AddDouble;
4367 append(isNaN, addOp, arg0, arg1, result);
4368 append(isNaN, Jump);
4369 isNaN->setSuccessors(continuation);
4370
4371 m_currentBlock = continuation;
4372
4373 return { };
4374}

4377{
4378 return addFloatingPointMinOrMax(Types::F32, MinOrMax::Max, arg0, arg1, result);
4379}

4398template<> auto AirIRGenerator::addOp<OpType::F32Copysign>(ExpressionType arg0, ExpressionType arg1, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
4399{
4400 // FIXME: We can have better codegen here for the imms and two operand forms on x86
4401 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=193999
4402 result = f32();
4403 auto temp1 = g32();
4404 auto sign = g32();
4405 auto value = g32();
4406
4407 // FIXME: Try to use Imm where possible:
4408 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=193999
4409 append(MoveFloatTo32, arg1, temp1);
4410 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(0x80000000), sign);
4411 append(And32, temp1, sign, sign);
4412
4413 append(MoveDoubleTo64, arg0, temp1);
4414 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(0x7fffffff), value);
4415 append(And32, temp1, value, value);
4416
4417 append(Or32, sign, value, value);
4418 append(Move32ToFloat, value, result);
4419
4420 return { };
4421}

4595template<> auto AirIRGenerator::addOp<OpType::F64Copysign>(ExpressionType arg0, ExpressionType arg1, ExpressionType& result) -> PartialResult
4596{
4597 // FIXME: We can have better codegen here for the imms and two operand forms on x86
4598 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=193999
4599 result = f64();
4600 auto temp1 = g64();
4601 auto sign = g64();
4602 auto value = g64();
4603
4604 append(MoveDoubleTo64, arg1, temp1);
4605 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(0x8000000000000000), sign);
4606 append(And64, temp1, sign, sign);
4607
4608 append(MoveDoubleTo64, arg0, temp1);
4609 append(Move, Arg::bigImm(0x7fffffffffffffff), value);
4610 append(And64, temp1, value, value);
4611
4612 append(Or64, sign, value, value);
4613 append(Move64ToDouble, value, result);
4614
4615 return { };
4616}
